name: Matthew McDonnell
text:
This was one of the most memorable experiences I have had after 4 years of living in Indonesia.  If you are interested in experiencing old Javanese culture, there is no better place to go.  I will never forget the experience of sitting next to the old men as they did their prayers over the tomb of the sultan, each one in his traditional clothing, carrying  kris, and speaking Javanese.

A few important points:
1.  This place lies at the intersection of history, religion, and culture generally.  It is not a tourist destination per se, and there is minimal signage explaining what things are.  Therefore, some basic homework beforehand will make the visit much more enjoyable.  It's a fascinating topic.

2. To enter the inner temple/tomb, you must change into traditional clothes (provided for a nominal fee) and put away all phones and cameras (photos in the outer area are fine).  These rules are strictly enforced and I've seen people refused entry for not changing their clothes.

3. Best time to go is when they are saying their prayers at tomb of Sultan Agung.  Please remember this is an extremely important religious ceremony for the local people and thus, it's critical to be respectful (e.g. quiet) and polite.  Everyone there I met was incredibly warm and happy to answer questions, although very few speak any English.
title: Makam Raja-Raja Imogiri

text: A holy place to embrace the glorious past and learning deeper about the history of Mataram Kingdom after Sultan Agung's reign. The whole hill is chosen by HRH Sultan Agung for himself and all of the Royal descendants from two kingdom; Surakarta & Yogyakarta. Have a look at the opening days & hours if you really want to visit the holy grave of Sultan Agung which the soil is smells very nice like perfume. After all, this place is a real place where authentic Royal Javanese culture (and sacred ritual) very well preserved.

name: Pudjo Basuki
text:
Minggu, 14 Juli 2024

Setelah selesai mengikuti pertemuan trah Suryobrangtan - Sri Sultan HB III di nDalem Bupati Puroloyo, dilanjutkan kesini untuk berziarah ke leluhur kami, Sri Sultan HB I (Sultan Agung Hanyokrokusumo), Sri Sultan HB III & KPH Suryobrongto.

Kami juga ditemani Romo Pinten, Pengageng Pajimatan Imogiri yang kebetulan masih kerabat kami.

Setelah berganti kostum yang memang diwajibkan untuk para peziarah, yaitu surjan dan jarik untuk kakung dan untuk putri berupa kemben dan jarik, kami masuk pintu dan naik ke pemakaman.
Oya, tarif menyewa kostum cukup murah yaitu 15k saja.

Ada dua pintu makam yang kami masuki.
Pintu makam Sultan Agung Hanyokrokusumo dan pintu makam Sultan HB III yang satu area dengan KPH Suryobrongto.
Di area makam, untuk menjaga kesakralan, peziarah tidak boleh pepotoan.

Pengalaman baru bagi kami adalah saat berada di makam Sultan Agung Hanyokrokusumo, ada tradisi mencium tanah di samping kiri nisan beliau yang berbau harum dan menghirup aroma wangi tersebut sebanyak tujuh kali, yang konon, panyuwunan kita akan terkabul.

Pengalaman lainnya adalah, kami berenam yang usianya berkisar 45 - 60 th, merasakan bagaimana kami harus ndungkluk dan mlumpat maju, mlaku ndhodhok saat hendak memasuki ruang makam lalu ndungkluk lagi dan mlumpat mundur ketika akan keluar dari ruang makam.
Serta mata dalam kondisi gelap mode on saat berziarah karena di dalam ruang makam sama sekali tidak ada lampu, hanya diterangi oleh cahaya lilin.
Yang artinya, gerak motorik kasar dan penglihatan kami harus ekstra 😁

Ok, segitu dulu cerita pengalaman kami.
Salam budaya, lestari budayaku.
Rahayu Sagung Dumadi🙏🏻
textTranslated:
Sunday, July 14 2024

After completing the Suryobrangtan - Sri Sultan HB III breed meeting at nDalem Regent Puroloyo, we continued here to make a pilgrimage to our ancestors, Sri Sultan HB I (Sultan Agung Hanyokrokusumo), Sri Sultan HB III & KPH Suryobrongto.

We were also accompanied by Romo Pinten, Pengageng Pajimatan Imogiri who happened to be our relative.

After changing into costumes which are mandatory for pilgrims, namely surjan and jarik for the kale and for the princess in the form of kemben and jarik, we entered the door and went up to the cemetery.
Oh yes, the cost of renting costumes is quite cheap, namely only 15k.

There are two doors to the tomb that we entered.
The door to the tomb of Sultan Agung Hanyokrokusumo and the door to the tomb of Sultan HB III which are in the same area as KPH Suryobrongto.
In the grave area, to maintain its sacredness, pilgrims are not allowed to take photos.

A new experience for us was when we were at the tomb of Sultan Agung Hanyokrokusumo, there was a tradition of kissing the ground on the left side of his tomb which smelled good and inhaling the aroma seven times, which was said to make our contemplation come true.

Another experience was that the six of us, whose ages ranged from 45 - 60, felt how we had to duck and jump forward, stumble when we were about to enter the tomb, then duck again and jump backwards when we were about to leave the tomb.
And the eyes are in dark mode when making a pilgrimage because there are absolutely no lights in the tomb room, it is only lit by candlelight.
Which means, our gross motor movements and vision have to be extra 😁

OK, that's all about our experience.
Cultural greetings, preserve my culture.
Rahayu Sagung Dumadi🙏🏻

Minggu, 7 Juli 2024.
Makam Raja Pajimatan Imogiri terletak di Dusun Pajimatan, Girirejo, Imogiri, Bantul. Posisi makam ini terletak sekitar 17 kilometer sebelah selatan pusat kota Yogyakarta. Letak kompleks makam ini berada di puncak Bukit Merak dengan ketinggian 85 meter di atas permukaan air laut.

Kompleks Makam Pajimatan Imogiri ini merupakan makam-makam dari raja keturunan Mataram mulai dari masa Mataram Islam hingga masa kerajaan terbagi menjadi dua Yogyakarta dan Surakarta.
textTranslated:
Sunday, July 7, 2024.
The tomb of King Pajimatan Imogiri is located in Pajimatan Hamlet, Girirejo, Imogiri, Bantul. The position of this tomb is located about 17 kilometers south of the city center of Yogyakarta. The location of this tomb complex is at the top of Merak Hill with a height of 85 meters above sea level.

The Pajimatan Imogiri Tomb Complex is the tombs of kings of Mataram descent from the Islamic Mataram period until the kingdom was divided into two, Yogyakarta and Surakarta.

text:
Masya Allah akhir nya bisa ziaroh ke makam Raja Raja Imogiri, semoga arwah2 nya husnul khotimah dan di tempat di surga terbaik aamiin

Untuk menuju makam menempuh kurleb 30-40menit kalau jalan kaki kurleb 454 anak tangga sungguh melelahkan bukan?

Jadi ada solusi lain untuk naik ojek ges, ya hitung2 bantu perekonomian warlok gpp kan? Murah kok tarif ojek nya 10k dan rata2 itu supir nya ibu2 semua masya Allah keren👍

Jangan lupa kalau pas naik ojek pegangan ya ges, ngebut bangetttt supir nyaa wkwk mana tanjakan nya agak curam sihh top lah warlok nya.

Untuk berkunjung ke makam harus reservasi dulu ges, soal nya tutup cuma smpe jam 13.00 kalo gak salah ya. Terus juga banyak aturan yg harus di patuhi saat berkunjung, salah satu nya memakai baju adat abdi dalem.

Kalau mau ziaroh ke makam untuk wanita yg berhijab wajib di buka😭 memakai kemben & kebaya, untuk laki2 nya memakai kain & baju khas Jogja serta blangkon. Btw ada tarif sewa baju nya ya ges kalo gak salah 15-30rb an deh.

Indah nya perjalanan sejarah Islam di Tanah Jawa, belajar sejarah nya dapet, wisata nya dapet. Jogja memang Istimewa🥰💖👍
textTranslated:
Masha Allah, finally we can visit the tomb of Raja Raja Imogiri, may his soul be blessed and in the best place in heaven, aamiin

To get to the tomb, it takes 30-40 minutes, walking up 454 steps is really tiring, isn't it?

So there is another solution to riding a motorbike taxi, so it's a good idea to help Warlok's economy, right? How cheap is the motorbike taxi fare of 10k and on average the drivers are all ladies, masha Allah, cool👍

Don't forget that when you get on a motorbike taxi, the handle is tight, the driver is really speeding, wow, the incline is a bit steep, he's a top driver.

To visit the tomb you have to make a reservation first, bro, it only closes until 13.00 if I'm not mistaken. Then there are also many rules that must be obeyed when visiting, one of which is wearing traditional abdi dalem clothes.

If you want to visit the grave, women who wear the hijab must remove it😭 wear a kemben & kebaya, for men wear typical Jogja cloth & clothes and blangkon. BTW, there is a clothing rental rate, if I'm not mistaken, it's around 15-30 thousand.

The beauty of the journey of Islamic history in the Land of Java, you can learn history, you can get tourism. Jogja is indeed special🥰💖👍

name: Soneo
text:
kompleks makam Raja-Raja Mataram Islam beserta keturunannya, yaitu raja-raja yang bertahta di Kasunanan Surakarta dan Kasultanan Yogyakarta.
Kesini niat dari rumah memang mau wisata religi sekalian ziarah.
Untuk tempatnya luas, saat masuk akan disuguhi anak tangga sekitar 400an. Ada penjual makanan di pinggir an dan diatas jadi tidak perlu khawatir jika tidak bawa minum.
Khusus untuk makam sultan agung hanya sampai jam 1 dan jika mau ke makamnya wajib pakai setelan adat jawa pakai blangkon dan tidak boleh pakai alas kaki. Disini sudah disediakan pakaiannya. Untuk sewa kalau tidak salah sekitar 15k. Dan saat ke makam sultan agung tidak boleh mengambil foto jadi hanya bisa foto diluar saja.
Tips kalau mau ke makam sultan agung sedia uang recehan karena akan ada kotak amal pendaftaran dan diatas juga ada tapi seihklasnya.
textTranslated:
the tomb complex of the Islamic Kings of Mataram and their descendants, namely the kings who reigned in Kasunanan Surakarta and Yogyakarta Sultanate.
The intention of coming here from home was to do religious tourism as well as a pilgrimage.
The place is spacious, when you enter you will be presented with around 400 steps. There are food vendors on the sides and above so you don't need to worry if you don't bring something to drink.
Especially for the tomb of the great sultan, it is only until 1 o'clock and if you want to go to his tomb, you must wear a traditional Javanese suit, wearing a blangkon and you cannot wear footwear. Here the clothes are provided. For rent, if I'm not mistaken, around 15k. And when you go to the tomb of the Great Sultan you are not allowed to take photos so you can only take photos outside.
Tips: If you want to go to the tomb of the great sultan, prepare some change because there will be a charity registration box and there is one above too, but keep it simple.

text:
Banyak pungutan, tapi sukarela. Buat yang mau masuk melihat makam raja-raja harus sewa pakaian 15ribu per orang. Yang perempuan harus pakai kemben, dan yang berjilbab harus dibuka.

Sumbangan sukarela itu untuk abdi-abdi dalem yang mengurus pemakaman. Jadi seikhlasnya aja, lumayan untuk bantu-bantu mereka di sana

Menarik untuk belajar sejarah dan budaya masyarakatnya sekaligus mengingat kematian. Bahwa apa pun posisi atau jabatan kita, tua, muda, kaya, miskin semua akan menemui Nya. Yang muslimah, jangan sampai buka jilbab. Cukup sampai di pendopo saja

Hal gk menyenangkan, penjual sego pecel di tangga sebelum masuk kompleks pemakaman memberikan harga berbeda untuk orang dari luar kota dan dalam kota. Yang dari dalam kota, ditawari  sego pecel 5000 per porsi sementara kami 10ribu per porsi. Gak lagi-lagi deh beli makan di sekitar situ 😬
textTranslated:
Lots of fees, but voluntary. Those who want to go in to see the tombs of the kings must rent clothes for 15 thousand per person. Women must wear tube tops, and those wearing headscarves must be removed.

The voluntary donation was for the courtiers who took care of the funeral. So just be sincere, it's enough to help them there

It is interesting to learn about the history and culture of the people while remembering death. That whatever our position or position, old, young, rich, poor, all will meet Him. Muslim women, do not remove the hijab. Just get to the pavilion

What's not fun is that the sego pecel seller on the stairs before entering the cemetery complex gives different prices to people from outside the city and inside the city. Those from within the city were offered 5000 pecel per portion while we were 10 thousand per portion. I don't buy food around there anymore 😬

name: Adzlan Nf
text:
Pada akhir masa pemerintahannya, Sultan Agung memerintahkan Panembahan Juminah (paman Sultan Agung) untuk membangun Makam di Giriloyo Imogiri. Namun saat pembangunan makam belum selesai, Panembahan Juminah meninggal dunia dan dimakamkan di makam yang dibangunnya tersebut.

Sultan Agung kemudian memerintahkan Kyai Tumenggung Citrokusumo untuk membangun Makam di Pajimatan Imogiri yang dikenal dengan nama Makam Pajimatan Imogiri. Makam ini digunakan untuk memakamkan Sultan Agung dan raja-raja Mataram beserta keturunannya dan Sultan Agung adalah raja pertama yang dimakamkan di Makam Pajimatan Imogiri ini.

Kompleks Makam Pajimatan Imogiri terletak kurang lebih 20 kilometer ke arah tenggara dari pusat Kota Yogyakarta, tepatnya di wilayah Kalurahan/Desa Girirejo dan Kalurahan/Desa Wukirsari, Kapanewon/Kecamatan Imogiri, Kabupaten Bantul, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta.

Imogiri berasal dari kata hima dan giri. Hima berarti kabut dan giri berarti gunung, sehingga Imogiri bisa diartikan sebagai gunung yang diselimuti kabut.

Untuk mendapatkan informasi selengkapnya, silahkan kunjungi Makam Pajimatan Imogiri dan melakukan pemindaian QR Code pada masing-masing Penanda Keistimewaan yang berada di Makam Pajimatan Imogiri.
textTranslated:
At the end of his reign, Sultan Agung ordered Panembahan Juminah (Sultan Agung's uncle) to build a tomb at Giriloyo Imogiri. However, when the construction of the tomb was not finished, Panembahan Juminah died and was buried in the tomb he had built.

Sultan Agung then ordered Kyai Tumenggung Citrokusumo to build a tomb at Pajimatan Imogiri known as the Pajimatan Imogiri Tomb. This tomb was used to bury Sultan Agung and the kings of Mataram and their descendants and Sultan Agung was the first king to be buried in the Pajimatan Imogiri Tomb.

The Pajimatan Imogiri Tomb Complex is located approximately 20 kilometers to the southeast of the center of Yogyakarta City, precisely in the Kalurahan/Girirejo Village and Wukirsari Village, Kapanewon/Imogiri District, Bantul Regency, Special Region of Yogyakarta.

Imogiri comes from the words hima and giri. Hima means fog and giri means mountain, so Imogiri can be interpreted as a mountain covered in fog.

To get complete information, please visit the Pajimatan Imogiri Cemetery and scan the QR Code on each Special Marker at the Pajimatan Imogiri Cemetery.
title: Makam Raja-Raja Imogiri

Kotagede Tomb:
-	Located in Kotagede, about 5 km southeast of the center of Yogyakarta.
-	It is the resting place of the first kings of the Mataram Sultanate, including Panembahan Senopati, the founder of Islamic Mataram.
-	The complex also includes a mosque and a bustling traditional market.

These tombs not only have high historical value, but also become a place of pilgrimage and cultural tourism for many people.

text: A Great historical place that I've had ever visited through out the years. It located in the southern side of the city, nearby the traditional market. Most of people are known this area as "Kotagede" in bhaasa or Big City in English. I do really understand why should this place has its name. It's truly a big city with some markets, royal cemetery, big mosque & massive roundabout in the cornerstone. The cemetery.is part of mosque actually. It has lovely mixed architectural shapes through Islamic era & Hindi's perspective. No cover charge when entering this site, just pay for motor/car parking. But pls do no yelling and any other disturbing noise when we're here.

text:
If you like visiting historical sites, you are suitable for a trip to "Makan Raja-Raja Mataram Kotagede".

There is no entrance fee to enter this area. The location is mixed with the neighborhood, and there are several alleys of "Kampung Alun-Alun" which are indeed used as tourist attractions.

For foreign tourists, this place has been provided with information boards in English, so you can still learn the history and culture related to this location.
title: Makam Raja-Raja Mataram Kotagede

text: The cemetry of Mataram 1st King, Panembahan Senopati. A unique historical place in the heart of Kota Gede, one of most beautiful village in Jogja. The local residents are very welcome and friendly. You can take a lot of photo in here, but please be polite and behave :)
title: Makam Raja-Raja Mataram Kotagede

address: 59CX+3HP, Jl. Masjid Besar Mataram, Sayangan, Jagalan, Banguntapan, Bantul Regency, Special Region of Yogyakarta 55192, Indonesia
name: Brasukra G Sudjana
text:
A unique experience where visitors have to put on traditional Javanese dresses upon entering the cemetery. You have to pay for the dresses. In addition there are multiple forced "donations" requested throughout the place. We gave money at the front house before even renting the dresses. Then we pay again at the pendopo before the cemetery gate. There is at least one more payment inside the cemetery upon entry into one of the buildings. Finally we pay for the dresses when we were finished. They say it's "voluntary" donations and don't set a price, but they essentially won't let you in unless you pay. This attitude and practice is really off putting. If it's really voluntary they shouldn't force people to pay. And they could simplify the system by making just one mandatory payment.

Inside the building inside the cemetery there were tombs of Panembahan Senopati, founder of Moslem Mataram, his father, Ki Ageng Pemanahan, the king of Pajang, who gave them the land, and Ki Ageng Mangir, a chief of a nearby village who married Senopati's daughter but was killed by him.
title: Makam Raja-Raja Mataram Kotagede

text: I would suggest you to visit this first before you start your journey to know more about Java Islamic Kingdom, such as Kraton Yogyakarta, Kasunanan Surakarta, Pakualaman, and Mangkunegaraan. Because this is the old center of the Java Islamic Kingdom. There are three main attraction in this place, the mosque, the king thomb, and the bath palace. You can pay as you wish, but to enter the king thomb you need to wear the traditional clothes and you need to pay for the rent. You can see the albino cat fish, as one of their point of attraction. But, there’s no tour guide in here, which kind of confusing for me.

Parking is available. There are toilets. There is a mosque. The only thing you don't have is your hope of having it 😆

Pretty fun. One of the sacred places in Jogja that should not be missed is the Tomb of the Imogiri kings. Well, to get here you have to climb hundreds of stairs, which for a fat person like me is quite tiring.

Oh yes, you are not allowed to take pictures inside the tomb. And you have to wear clothes like this. So, apart from getting the vibe, you also get the content 😆 okay, sipz

text:

Berikut yang ada di kompleks pemakaman raja raja :
- pasar wisata
- parkir motor
- parkir bis

- penjual minuman yang ramah baik dan murah

Nah, karena di sini harus naik tangga cukup tinggi, kita kalau beli minum di penjual di atas saja karena harganya murah dan terjangkau.
textTranslated:
To enter the tomb, rent traditional clothing for 15 thousand
And open from 10.00 - 12.30
So come on time if you want to enter the tomb of the king.

Here's what's in the king's burial complex:
- tourist market
- Motorcycle Parking Only
- bus parking
- car park
- an ancient mosque that can be used for worship
- climb the stairs high enough to get to the top
- friendly and cheap drink seller

Well, because here we have to climb quite high stairs, we can just buy drinks from the seller above because the prices are cheap and affordable.

name: Mayang
text:
Makam raja-raja yang katanya banyak dikunjungi para pejabat atau orang-orang besar lainnya ketika mempunyai mempunyai hajat tertentu. Antara makam raja satu dengan raja yang lain dipisahkan dan ditandai dengan gapura besar. Untuk bisa masuk ke gapura atau makam raja tertentu, pengunjung harus memenuhi syarat diantara bagi pengunjung perempuan harus mengenakan pakaian jawa berupa kemben tanpa tambahan pakaian lain seperti jilbab.
Bagi pengunjung berhijab yang tidak bersedia mengenakan kemben tidak diperbolehkan masuk ke gapura dan hanya bisa berkeliling di area komplek makam.
textTranslated:
The tombs of kings are said to be visited by many officials or other big people when they have certain purposes. The tombs of one king and another are separated and marked by a large gate. To be able to enter the gate or tomb of a particular king, visitors must meet the requirements, including that female visitors must wear Javanese clothing in the form of a kemben without additional clothing such as a headscarf.
Visitors wearing the hijab who are not willing to wear a kemben are not allowed to enter the gate and can only walk around the tomb complex area.
title: Makam Raja-Raja Imogiri

textTranslated: Ample parking and there is a mosque at the entrance. We have to climb several stairs to get to the top. You have to be prepared to bring drinks because climbing the stairs is quite tiring. There are several sellers along the road to the tomb. It's better to come here in the morning because in the afternoon it feels very hot. The cemetery closing schedule is approximately 1 o'clock if you want to go inside.

address: 39HW+R83 Makam Raja-Raja Yogyakarta & Surakarta Pajimatan, Karang Kulon, Wukirsari, Kec. Imogiri, Kabupaten Bantul, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55782, Indonesia
name: i one
text:
Ongkos2 kurang transparant, waktu di bawah di cegat katanya hrs bayar buka portal dan administrasi masing2 50rb total 100rb, setelah bayar itu ditagih karcis parkir Rp 5000. Naik keatas di pandu mas2 yg awal tadi.

Diatas di jelaskan bla2 ... dan istirahat di bawah makam Sulatan Agung, kalo mau minum air gentong bayar seikhlasnya, karena sdh lewat jam 13 tdk bisa masuk ke makam, tapi bisa di usahakan asal ada 'ijin' ...

Pas mau pulang kita kasih tips 50rb utk pemandu nya, eh dia minta tambah katanya minimal tips 100rb ... hehehe

Jadi total biaya kunjungan ber lima Rp. 205.000

Sekedar pengetahuan saja, mungkin kedepan bisa transparat dan atau apa bisa ditawar ?
textTranslated:
The costs were not transparent, when I was stopped at the bottom, they said you had to pay, open the portal and administration, 50 thousand for a total of 100 thousand each, after paying, you were charged a parking ticket of IDR 5,000. Go upstairs, guided by the guys from earlier.

The above is explained in detail... and rest under the tomb of Sulatan Agung, if you want to drink barrel water, pay as willingly as possible, because after 13 o'clock you can't enter the tomb, but you can try as long as you have 'permission'...

When we were going home we gave a tip of 50 thousand to the guide, but he asked for more, he said the minimum tip was 100 thousand... hehehe

So the total cost of the five visits is IDR. 205,000

Just for knowledge, maybe in the future it can be transparent and or can it be negotiated?
title: Makam Raja-Raja Imogiri

Hai kamu apa kabar🤗semangat ibadah puasanya yaa skyy💙💪next kita olahraga bareng  disini ya🤩
textTranslated: Religious tourism or pilgrimage tourism should be more favored in this place, but the place is poorly maintained (it looks singup) perhaps because it is a tomb (?) even though it can be promising for both local residents and the local government. Thank God, the pandemic has had a positive side for the tombs of these kings because many cyclists visited, seeing local residents setting up stalls there again, I felt happy because usually this tomb is busy during Eid. I took a photo of the sky because the best thing in the morning is a clear sky, like it is very colorful in the morning. Hi, how are you 🤗 keep your fasting spirit, skyy 💙💪 next time we will exercise together here okay 🤩

text:

name: Muhammad Latif Nur Azmi
text: Makam Raja Raja Mataram di Pakistan Imogiri, makam ini merupakan makam dari beberapa raja yang pernah berkuasa dikerjakan Mataram, Surakarta dan Yogyakarta, di sini juga terdapat makam dari Sultan Agung yang merupakan raja paling terkenal di kerajaan Mataram Islam. Untuk akses di lokasi bisa terbilang mudah sampai ditempat parkir bawah kita akan disambut dengan ratusan anak tangga menuju kompleks pemakaman yang sering digunakan untuk olahraga naik turun tangga, tapi tenang saja bagi yang tidak kuat untuk naik ratusan anak tangga bisa memakai jasa ojek dari warga sekitar yang murah untuk harganya. Menuju lokasi makam banyak penjual oleh oleh dan makanan khas baik dari pecel kembang Turi maupun peyek tampah, dan juga minuman khas Imogiri yaitu wedang uwuh yang memiliki banyak khasiat untuk kesehatan karena banyak komposisi dari rempah rempah. Sesampainya di kompleks pemakaman terdapat joglo Sapit utang yang bisa digunakan untuk istirahat maupun ziarah, nah jika ingin berziarah sampai kepasareyan Sultan Agung maupun raja raja lain harus memakai baju adat Jawa yaitu Surjan dan Jarit untuk laki laki dan kemben untuk perempuan yang dimana di joglo Sapit utang disediakan untuk disewakan. Pengalaman kesini sangat memuaskan baik dari sisi religi maupun fisik . Tempat di kompleks makam Raja Raja Mataram juga cocok untuk berfoto dan mengabadikan momen bersama sama
textTranslated: Tomb of Raja Raja Mataram in Pakistan Imogiri, this tomb is the tomb of several kings who once ruled Mataram, Surakarta and Yogyakarta, here there is also the tomb of Sultan Agung who was the most famous king in the Islamic Mataram kingdom. Access to the location can be said to be easy, arriving at the lower parking lot we will be greeted with hundreds of stairs leading to the cemetery complex which is often used for sports going up and down stairs, but don't worry, for those who don't have the strength to climb hundreds of stairs, you can use the motorbike taxi services from local residents. cheap for the price. Towards the grave site, there are many sellers of souvenirs and typical food, both pecel kembang Turi and peyek tampah, and also the typical Imogiri drink, namely wedang uwuh, which has many health benefits because it contains many spices. When you arrive at the burial complex, there is a Sapit Debt joglo which can be used for rest or pilgrimage. So, if you want to make a pilgrimage to the market of Sultan Agung or other kings, you have to wear traditional Javanese clothes, namely Surjan and Jarit for men and kemben for women, which is in the Sapit Debt Joglo. provided for rent. The experience here is very satisfying both from a religious and physical perspective. The place in the tomb complex of Raja Raja Mataram is also suitable for taking photos and immortalizing moments together

name: galih akademik
text: id putra dari Sunan Kalijaga dengan Dewi Zaroh putri Maulana Ishak, yang mengemban syiar di seputaran Muria. Nama Muria diambil dari Bukit Moriah di Jerusalem. Komplek tidak hanya makam tetapi juga masjid karena dulu Sunan Muria membuat pesantren disini. Namun bangunan masjid yang diperkirakan sejak abad 15 dan makam semua telah berganti. Untuk foto bangunan tidak bisa karena padatnya tata letak pedagang, kecuali pakai drone. Di seputar makam dan masjid terdapat banyak makam prajurit punggawa dulu, termasuk Panembahan Penggulu Jogodipo putra sunan muria, putri Nastiti, dan putri kanjeng sunan yang makamnya dari Desa Bareng dipindahkan ke sini. Makam ramai di Kamis Legi dan Jumat Pahing. Untuk buka luwur makam di Bulan Sura. Komplek makam pada pintu keluar Amda akan mendapatkan gentong yang airnya sejuk keluar dari sumur dan tidak habis. Konon gentong ini digunakan untuk minum Sunan Muria. Semakin kesamping terdapat banyak watu lumpang dari berabad-abad yang lalu. Sekitar watu lumpang banyak uang yang disebarkan pengunjung, tidak tahu maksudnya apa. Muria juga terkenal dengan tanaman khas parijata yang berkhasiat dan umbi janglong. Dari pusat kota Kudus sekitar 45 menit. #literasyikgalih #kilasdokumenter @galih.wib
textTranslated: id son of Sunan Kalijaga with Dewi Zaroh daughter of Maulana Ishak, who carries out preaching around Muria. The name Muria is taken from Mount Moriah in Jerusalem. The complex is not only a tomb but also a mosque because Sunan Muria used to build an Islamic boarding school here. However, the mosque building which is thought to date back to the 15th century and the tombs have all changed. It's not possible to take photos of the building because of the dense layout of the traders, unless you use a drone. Around the cemetery and mosque there are many graves of former retainer soldiers, including Panembahan Penggulu Jogodipo, son of Sunan Muria, daughter Nastiti, and daughter Kanjeng Sunan whose graves were moved here from Bareng Village. The graveyard is busy on Thursday Legi and Friday Pahing. To open the tomb in Bulan Sura. The tomb complex at the exit of Amda will have a barrel with cool water coming out of the well and it won't run out. It is said that this barrel was used to drink Sunan Muria. Further to the side there are many mortar stones from centuries ago. Around Watu Lumpang, visitors scatter a lot of money, they don't know what it means. Muria is also famous for its nutritious parijata plants and janglong tubers. From the center of Kudus city about 45 minutes. #literasyikgalih #kilasdocumenter @galih.wib
title: Tomb of Sunan Muria

Saat hari-hari biasa tempat ini juga masih ramai lenunjung.
Fasilitas di sini sangat lengkap. Mulai dari tempat ibadah yg bersih. Sumber Air yg melimpah serta Terdapat sumber mata air panas yg konon katanya bisa menyembuhkan berbagai macam penyakit bila kita mandi di sana

textTranslated:
Religious tourist attractions located in Wonobodro District, Blado District, Batang Regency
During certain events, this place is very crowded with pilgrims.
On normal days this place is still busy with visitors.
The facilities here are very complete. Starting from a clean place of worship. There are abundant water sources and there are hot springs which are said to be able to cure various diseases if we bathe there
If there is a pilgrimage event. Visitors can find many typical Wonobodro snacks such as opak emping etc. And if there are pilgrims who want to stay there. Local residents usually provide a place to rest for pilgrims and free food for pilgrims to sleep in the homes of the residents there. And that has become a tradition for the residents of the Ds. Wonobodro area.

address: Wonobodro, Blado, Batang Regency, Central Java 51255, Indonesia
name: Izza Kham
text:
Tempat ziarah dengan suasana sejuk karena di daerah dataran tinggi. Lokasinya di Kec. Blado, Kab. Batang. Rute nya sama seperti rute menuju ke kebun teh Pagilaran. Hanya saja untuk ke makam Wonobodro belok kanan.
Untuk biaya masuk biasanya gratis. Jika kita datang saat momen2 sepi, kita bisa naik kendaraan hingga ke area dekat makam (sebelum tangga gerbang makam). Namun jika kita datang saat momen ramai (seperti saat khoul) kita harus parkir jauh dari lokasi makam, dan berjalan beberapa kilometer. Khoul di makam Wonobodro  dilaksanakan pada bulan Muharram/ Suro.
Saat berkunjung pada waktu menjelang/saat khoul, akan ada banyak pedagang di kiri kanan jalan. Oleh2 yang khas dari Wonobodro adalah opak (sejenis keripik) singkong/ opak kentang 😁.
Untuk fasilitas lengkap, masjid, tempat wudlu, toilet, kamar mandi, dan tempat informasi. Suasana di sini dingin ya, apalagi saat malam hari. Jadi jangan lupa sedia jaket 😁
Selamat berkunjung, selamat beribadah. Semoga dapat meningkatkan ketaqwaan kita pada Allah SWT 😊
textTranslated:
A pilgrimage place with a cool atmosphere because it is in a highland area. The location is in Kec. Blado, Kab. Stem. The route is the same as the route to the Pagilaran tea plantation. It's just that to go to the Wonobodro cemetery, turn right.
Entrance fees are usually free. If we come at quiet moments, we can take a vehicle to the area near the tomb (before the stairs to the tomb gate). However, if we come at a busy moment (such as during khoul) we have to park far from the grave site and walk several kilometers. Khoul at the Wonobodro grave is held in the month of Muharram/Suro.
When visiting before/during khoul, there will be lots of traders on both sides of the road. A typical souvenir from Wonobodro is cassava opak (a type of chip)/potato opak 😁.
For complete facilities, mosque, ablution area, toilet, bathroom and information area. The atmosphere here is cold, especially at night. So don't forget to prepare a jacket 😁
Welcome, happy worship. Hopefully it can increase our devotion to Allah SWT 😊
title: Makam Syeikh Maulana Al Maghribi

text:
Alfatehah.
Salah satu Makam Waliyulloh yang paling sepuh (tua) di tanah Jawa. Beliau berasal dari kota kecil Maghrib di Maroko, Afrika. Kalau ditelusuri sejarahnya Makam ini lebih tua dari zaman Syech Abdul Qodir Al Jailani. semasa hidup Syech Abdul Qodir Al Jailani juga konon sering berziarah ke Makam Syeikh Maulana Al Maghribi ini.
Karena beliau adalah masih Gurunya.
Banyak bukti dimana-mana sejarah ulama penyiar Islam banyak yang berasal dari Maroko Afrika.
Konon dahulu lokasi ini yang masih hutan belantara sering dijadikan sebagai tempat bertemunya seluruh Wali2 di tanah Jawa.
Karena lokasinya yang berada di lereng perbukitan jadi udaranya otomatis sejuk sekali, sangat damai.
Uniknya, di lokasi Makam ini tidak ada satu pun peminta2.
Rata2 anak kecil dan mereka pasti jualan air putih dalam botol aqua bekas. Air putih itu diambil dari pancuran mata air yang konon dulu sering dijadikan tempat Wudlu Syeikh Maulana Al Maghrobi/ Al Maghribi. Padahal tempat wudlu ini dekat sekali dan terlihat oleh peziarah ckckck. Tidak apa2 kalau kita mau berbagi rezeki sedikit dengan mereka. Mereka akan sangat senang sekali kalau kita membeli airnya.
Jajanannya pun sangat-sangat murah sekali, nasi jagung urap sama rempeyek ikan asin aja gak sampai 5ribu, kenyang.
Selain itu jajanan oleh2 khas Wonobodro adalah opak singkong yang lebar2 & talas ubi rebus yang sangat murah harganya. Subhanallah..
textTranslated:
Alfatehah.
One of the oldest Waliyulloh graves in Java. He comes from the small town of Maghrib in Morocco, Africa. If you trace the history of this tomb, it is older than the time of Syech Abdul Qodir Al Jailani. During the life of Syech Abdul Qodir Al Jailani, it is said that he often made pilgrimages to the grave of Sheikh Maulana Al Maghribi.
Because he is still his teacher.
There is a lot of evidence everywhere about the history of Islamic broadcasting clerics, many of whom came from Morocco, Africa.
It is said that in the past this location, which was still a wilderness, was often used as a meeting place for all the Guardians in Java.
Because the location is on a hillside, the air is automatically very cool, very peaceful.
Uniquely, at the location of this grave there was not a single beggar.
The average child is small and they definitely sell water in used aqua bottles. The white water was taken from a spring fountain which is said to have often been used as a place for ablution for Sheikh Maulana Al Maghrobi/Al Maghribi. Even though this ablution place is very close and can be seen by pilgrims tskckck. It's okay if we want to share a little fortune with them. They will be very happy if we buy the water.
The snacks are very, very cheap, corn rice and salted fish rempeyek alone don't cost 5 thousand, you're full.
Apart from that, Wonobodro's typical souvenir snacks are wide cassava opak & boiled sweet potato taro which are very cheap. Subhanallah..
title: Makam Syeikh Maulana Al Maghribi

Di komplek makam ini, selain makam beliau ada jg makam tokoh² besar Islam lain spt Kyai Ageng Pekalongan,Kyai Ageng Wonobodro,dll.

Selain di Wonobodro Batang, ada juga tempat lain yg dianggap sebagai makam dari Syeikh Maulana Magribi ini, diantaranya ada di Cirebon, di Parangtritis Yogyakarta, di Pantaran Boyolali, di Bayat Klaten, di Pekalongan dan di Tuban.

Mnrt slh satu versi, beliau merupakan salah satu dari anggota Wali Penyebar Islam di Jawa dari Angkatan ke-1 (1404 – 1435 M) yang terdiri dari Maulana Malik Ibrahim (wafat 1419), Maulana Ishaq, Maulana Ahmad Jumadil Kubro, Maulana Muhammad Al-Maghrabi, Maulana Malik Isra’il (wafat 1435), Maulana Muhammad Ali Akbar (wafat 1435), Maulana Hasanuddin, Maulana ‘Aliyuddin, dan Syekh Subakir(Syaikh Muhammad Al-Baqir).
Stlh generasi mereka, baru diteruskan oleh Walisongo yg kita kenal.
textTranslated:
In this tomb complex, apart from his tomb, there are also tombs of other great Islamic figures such as Kyai Ageng Pekalongan, Kyai Ageng Wonobodro, etc.

Apart from Wonobodro Batang, there are also other places which are considered to be the tomb of Sheikh Maulana Magribi, including in Cirebon, in Parangtritis Yogyakarta, in Pantaran Boyolali, in Bayat Klaten, in Pekalongan and in Tuban.

According to one version, he was one of the members of the Guardians for the Spread of Islam in Java from the 1st Generation (1404 – 1435 AD) consisting of Maulana Malik Ibrahim (d. 1419), Maulana Ishaq, Maulana Ahmad Jumadil Kubro, Maulana Muhammad Al- Maghrabi, Maulana Malik Isra'il (d. 1435), Maulana Muhammad Ali Akbar (d. 1435), Maulana Hasanuddin, Maulana 'Aliyuddin, and Sheikh Subakir (Shaykh Muhammad Al-Baqir).
After their generation, it was continued by the Walisongo that we know.

text: Sunan muria atau yang dikenal dengan nama Raden Umat said merupakan salah satu dari wali songo/wali sembilan yang menyebarkan dakwah islam di tanah jawa tepatnya di kota kudus. Makam beliau berada di atas gugung muria. Selain makam ada juga masjid yang merupakan peninggalan beliau. Karena lokasinya di atas gunung untuk mencapai tempat ini peziarah bisa naik ojek dengan tarif 20rb per orang untuk sekali jalan atau jalan naik anak tangga sampai pucuk. Jika naik ojek pastikan anda harus pegangan erat kepada pengemudi krn jalan yang begitu ekstrim. Untuk menuju makan ketika sudah di atas, peziarah harus menusuri lorong yang berada di dalam masjid sampai ke petilasan/makam. Setelah berdoa di makam silahkan beramal lah sesuai kemampuam dengan memasukan di kotak amal yang sudah di sediakan pengurus makam. Dan ketika keluar dari makam akan ketemu sumur/mata air karomah yang mana bisa di minum langsung atau di bawa pulang. Untuk menuju bawah paling enak jalan kaki sambil bisa beli oleh oleh atau cindera mata khas kota kudus. Tapi untuk orang tua atau sepuh tidak di sarankan untuk jalan karena medan jalan terlalu curam dan bahaya untuk orang tua. Untuk harga cendramata atau oleh terjangkau. Makam ini hampir setiap hari dalam 24 jam ramai akan peziarah dari seluruh penjuru. Untuk parkir sangat luas dan banyak pilihan. Untuk fasilitas disana berbayar dari 2rb sampai 5rb. Udara di sana juga enak, seger dan bersih. Dari makam juga kita bisa melihat seluruh kota kudus. Selamat mencoba
textTranslated: Sunan Muria or known as Raden Umat Said is one of the wali songo/wali nine who spread Islamic da'wah in Java, precisely in the holy city. His grave is on the gugung muria. Apart from the tomb, there is also a mosque which is his legacy. Because it is located on top of a mountain, to reach this place, pilgrims can take a motorbike taxi at a rate of 20 thousand per person for one way or climb the stairs to the top. If you take a motorbike taxi, make sure you hold tightly to the driver because the road is so extreme. To get to food when they are at the top, pilgrims must follow the corridor inside the mosque to the shrine/tomb. After praying at the grave, please do charity according to your ability by putting it in the charity box provided by the grave caretaker. And when you leave the tomb you will find a karomah well/spring which you can drink directly or take home. To get to the bottom, it's best to walk while you can buy souvenirs or souvenirs typical of the holy city. But it is not recommended for elderly or elderly people to walk because the terrain is too steep and dangerous for elderly people. For souvenir or affordable prices. This tomb is busy almost every day for 24 hours with pilgrims from all over. Parking is very spacious and lots of choices. The fees there are paid from 2 thousand to 5 thousand. The air there is also delicious, fresh and clean. From the tomb we can also see the entire holy city. good luck

name: Samfira Channel
text:
Dirangkum dari buku Sejarah Islam Indonesia karya Rizem Aizid dan buku Seri Jejak Para Wali: Sunan Kalijaga karya Lilis Suryani, Sunan Muria atau Raden Umar Said adalah putra dari Sunan Kalijaga dengan Dewi Saroh. Sunan Muria mengikuti jejak ayahnya sebagai juru dakwah di tanah Jawa. Ia juga adalah penyokong Kerajaan Demak Bintara yang setia dan juga berpartisipasi dalam pembangunan Masjid Agung Demak.

Sunan Muria berdakwah dengan cara yang halus. Cara tersebut digunakannya dalam menyiarkan Islam di sekitar Gunung Muria.

Metode dakwah Sunan Muria yaitu dengan menggunakan kesenian dan tradisi kebudayaan Jawa. Misalnya adat kenduri pada hari-hari tertentu setelah kematian anggota keluarga, seperti nelung dina (tiga harian), sampai nyewu (seribu hari) yang tidak diharamkannya. Hanya tradisi yang berbau klenik seperti membakar kemenyan atau menyuguhkan sesaji diganti dengan doa atau sholawat.

Sunan Muria juga berdakwah dengan menggunakan gamelan dan wayang. Hal ini dilakukan oleh Sunan Muria sebagai upaya mempertahankan metode dakwah ayahnya terdahulu.
textTranslated:
Summarized from the book History of Indonesian Islam by Rizem Aizid and the book Series Traces of the Guardians: Sunan Kalijaga by Lilis Suryani, Sunan Muria or Raden Umar Said is the son of Sunan Kalijaga and Dewi Saroh. Sunan Muria followed in his father's footsteps as a preacher in Java. He was also a loyal supporter of the Demak Bintara Kingdom and also participated in the construction of the Demak Grand Mosque.

Sunan Muria preached in a subtle way. He used this method to broadcast Islam around Mount Muria.

Sunan Muria's method of preaching was to use Javanese arts and cultural traditions. For example, there are kenduri customs on certain days after the death of a family member, such as nelung dina (three days), to nyewu (one thousand days) which are not forbidden. Only traditions that are occult, such as burning incense or presenting offerings, are replaced with prayers or prayers.

Sunan Muria also preached using gamelan and wayang. This was done by Sunan Muria as an effort to maintain his father's previous preaching methods.
title: Tomb of Sunan Muria

address: 8VMX+FHJ, jl terminal wisata, Colo, Kec. Dawe, Kabupaten Kudus, Jawa Tengah 59353, Indonesia
name: Faisal Reza Sukmawan
text:
Obyek wisata religi ini berada di ketinggian yaitu puncak bukit Muria, jalan menuju makam bisa diakses dengan berjalan kaki melewati ratusan anak tangga yang menanjak curam ataupun via ojek, tarif ojek saat ini yaitu naik menuju makam Rp. 25000 dan turun Rp 10000, disini selalu ramai dengan peziarah yang datang dari berbagai daerah, terlebih di hari-hari tertentu biasanya lebih banyak rombongan yang datang.
Untuk penggemar tracking maupun kuat secara fisik, jalan kaki sepertinya pilihan tepat karena bisa juga hitung-hitung sambil berolahraga. Khusus untuk penumpang ojek supaya pengunjung/peziarah agak berhati-hati dan siap mental karena medannya memang berkelok juga menukik dengan gaya mengemudi driver ojek yang tergolong ekstrim dan memacu adrenalin.
textTranslated:
This religious tourist attraction is located at a height, namely the top of Muria Hill, the road to the tomb can be accessed by walking through hundreds of steeply ascending stairs or via motorbike taxi, the current motorbike taxi fare is Rp. 25,000 and down Rp. 10,000, here it is always busy with pilgrims coming from various regions, especially on certain days usually more groups come.
For tracking fans and those who are physically strong, walking seems like the right choice because you can also do calculations while exercising. Especially for motorbike taxi passengers, visitors/pilgrims should be a bit careful and mentally prepared because the terrain is indeed winding and dips with the driving style of motorbike taxi drivers which is considered extreme and adrenaline pumping.
title: Tomb of Sunan Muria

Tp setelah sampai sana Alhamdulillah langsung lega liat view dari atas. Airnya dingin banget, meskipun ngga weekend tp bnyak juga yg ziarah ke sini. Oh ya jangan lupa minum air digentong makam sunan muria dan beli pentol muria ygy😭🤣
textTranslated: The first time I came here I was invited by a friend, on the way to his grave, Montoran was riding on a piggyback ride with a friend, but I was really scared because the road kept going up and up and had lots of sharp turns😭 it made my heart beat. But after arriving there, Alhamdulillah, I was immediately relieved to see the view from above. The water is really cold, even though it's not a weekend, many people make pilgrimages here. Oh yes, don't forget to drink water at Sunan Muria's grave and buy a Muria pentol 😭🤣

address: 8VMX+FHJ, jl terminal wisata, Colo, Kec. Dawe, Kabupaten Kudus, Jawa Tengah 59353, Indonesia
name: Agung Ribowo
text:
Sunan muria merupakan salah satu tokoh penting. Salah satu dari sembilan wali atau disebut nama lain walisongo. Wali yang menyebarkan agama Islam di pulau Jawa. Dengan adanya wali songo penyebaran agama Islam di pulau Jawa semakin banyak. Dan semakin meluasnya penyebaran agama Islam di pulang jawa. Pada jaman dahulu pusat pemerintahan pada kesultanan Demak.

Makam Sunan Muria, makam terletak berada diatas bukit muria. Makam didalamnya menggunakan banyak kayu ukir ukiran. Hampir sebagian besar didalam makam menggunakan kayu. Untuk menuju ke atas makam bisa dengan berjalan melalui tangga, atau menggunakan transportasi ojek.
textTranslated:
Sunan Muria is one of the important figures. One of the nine guardians or also known as walisongo. Wali who spread Islam on the island of Java. With the existence of Wali Songo, the spread of Islam on the island of Java increased. And the increasingly widespread spread of Islam in Java. In ancient times the center of government was the Demak sultanate.

Sunan Muria Tomb, the tomb is located on Muria Hill. The tomb inside uses a lot of carved wood carvings. Most of the tombs use wood. To get to the top of the tomb, you can walk up the stairs or use a motorbike taxi.
title: Tomb of Sunan Muria

Karena kesini pada saat makan siang, kami pun mencoba berbagai jajanan mulai dr Tahu Gejrot, Es Kuwut Bali, Es Cendol Ireng, Es Goyang, Gulali bentuk, Es Kopi Tarik, Pukis Keju, Nasi Kucing & Usus, Sego Berkat & Gorengannya.

Selain stand makanan juga ada stand kerajinan tradisional seperti batik dan lainnya.

Here, when the 212th Anniversary of the Pakualaman Duchy was held, the Sewandanan Market contained various traditional snack stands from Yogyakarta and also from other regions.

Because we were here at lunch time, we also tried various snacks starting from Tahu Gejrot, Es Kuwut Bali, Es Cendol Ireng, Es Goyang, Cotton candy, Tarik Ice Coffee, Cheese Pukis, Nasi Cat & Intestine, Sego Berkat & Fried.

Apart from food stands, there are also traditional craft stands such as batik and others.

name: Much Ae
text: Makam dari raja-raja mataraman dari keraton jogjakarta dan solo, suasana yg khas dengan adat jawa dan klasikal. Dibukaya malam imogiri sebagai wisata religi sangat bagus bagi generasi muda untuk tau bahwa banyak dari leluhur kita yg sangat luar biasa dlm kemajuan peradaban yg ada di Indonesia khususnya tanah jawa. Tdk bisa dipungkiri bahwa raja-raja dari yogjakarta dan solo sangat berpengaruh masa dahulu dalam memperjuangkan NKRI. Generasi muda saat ini perlu melihat kebelakang sedikit agar tdk kalah dengan leluhur yg telah membuat prestasi yg sangat besar.
textTranslated: The tombs of the Mataraman kings from the Jogjakarta and Solo palaces, a typical atmosphere with Javanese and classical traditions. Opening the Imogiri night as a religious tourism is very good for the younger generation to know that many of our ancestors were extraordinary in the advancement of civilization in Indonesia, especially Java. It cannot be denied that the kings of Yogyakarta and Solo were very influential in the past in fighting for the Republic of Indonesia. Today's young generation needs to look back a little so as not to lose out to their ancestors who have made enormous achievements.
title: Makam Raja-Raja Imogiri

textTranslated: for those of you who want religious tourism... more precisely to remember that we will not live forever, I highly recommend that you take a trip to the grave of Sheikh Maulana Al Maghrobi which is located in Wonobodro Village, Blado District, Batang Regency, Central Java, there I'm sure you will definitely remember Lord. Apart from the friendly residents in the parking area, some of the residents are selling typical food from Wonobodro and in the month of As Surok or the month in the Hijri calendar, Wonobodro is very busy with pilgrims because in that month the local community commemorates KAKHOL for Sheikh Maulana Al Maghrobi, in starting from the first until the peak event on the thirteenth of that Sunday, what made me even more impressed was that all the residents' houses had their doors wide open specifically to receive guests from outside the area as a form of respect for the guests, many of whom were khabaib and clerics who were present to send prayers or pray for Sheikh Maulana Al Maghrobi to receive blessings from Sheikh Maulana Al Maghrobi and there is not only one GUARDIAN OF ALLAH there but many, maybe this is all I can review about the grave of Sheikh Maulana Al Maghrobi if you are interested in that place You can come straight to the place, that's enough and thank you.

name: ahmad n
text:
Udaranya segar dan tempatnya sejuk karena lokasinya berada di lereng perbukitan. Sumber airnya melimpah, tapi ada satu tempat yang dipercaya sebagai Air Keramat karena dahulu tempat itu digunakan oleh para Auliya (khususnya Syeikh Maulana Maghribi) untuk wudhu.
Karena banyak peziarah yang datang dari berbagai tempat maka banyak pedagang disana (baik dari Wonobodro maupun luar Wonobodro) sehingga roda perekonomian masyarakat (khususnya lokal) berjalan dengan baik.
Walaupun terletak diperbukitan, tapi akses masuk ke sana tidaklah sulit karena dari tahun ke tahun infrastruktur disana selalu mengalami perbaikan.
textTranslated:
The air is fresh and the place is cool because the location is on a hillside. The water sources are abundant, but there is one place that is believed to be Sacred Water because that place was previously used by the Auliya (especially Sheikh Maulana Maghribi) for ablution.
Because many pilgrims come from various places, there are many traders there (both from Wonobodro and outside Wonobodro) so that the economy of the community (especially local) runs well.
Even though it is located in the hills, access to it is not difficult because from year to year the infrastructure there is always improving.
title: Makam Syeikh Maulana Al Maghribi

name: Mustafa Ammar S
text: Makam Raja Mataram di Kotagede adalah situs bersejarah yang menawarkan pengalaman spiritual dan kultural yang mendalam. Tempat ini sangat terawat dengan baik dan penuh dengan nuansa sejarah yang kental. Arsitekturnya yang khas dengan ornamen-ornamen tradisional Jawa membuat suasana semakin sakral. Pengunjung dapat merasakan kedamaian dan keheningan saat berjalan di area makam, sekaligus mengenal lebih dekat sejarah kerajaan Mataram. Petugas dan pemandu yang ramah dan informatif menambah nilai kunjungan. Tempat ini sangat direkomendasikan bagi mereka yang ingin memahami lebih dalam sejarah dan budaya Jawa.
textTranslated: The Tomb of the Mataram King in Kotagede is a historical site that offers a deep spiritual and cultural experience. This place is very well maintained and full of a strong sense of history. The distinctive architecture with traditional Javanese ornaments makes the atmosphere even more sacred. Visitors can feel peace and silence when walking in the tomb area, as well as get to know more closely the history of the Mataram kingdom. Friendly and informative officers and guides add value to the visit. This place is highly recommended for those who want to understand more deeply the history and culture of Java.
title: Makam Raja-Raja Mataram Kotagede

name: galih akademik
text:
Makam Kota Gede ini konon sekomplek dengan keraton Mataram Islam. Berada di barat Masjid Agung Kota Gede, makam ini disebut Pasarean Hastana Kitha Ageng. komplek makam ini terdiri dari masjid, sendang pemandian putri yang memiliki sumber air dari pohon beringin di sekitarnya dan pemandian putra serta makam pendiri mataram, yaitu Ki Ageng Pemanahan, Panembahan Senopati raja I pendiri Mataram, Sultan Hamengkubuwono II, Pakualam I-IV serta kerabat. Makam masuk dalam wilayah Dusun Sayangan, Jagalan, Banguntapan, Kabupaten Bantul, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta.
Di dalam juga tersapat bangsal Prbayaksa, Witana dan Tajug. Masuk makam harus menggunakan pakaian adat. Suasana cukup teduh dam cocok untuk spot foto. Bangunan yang masih bercorak Hindu di tengah kerajaan Islam ini dibangun tahun 1589 menurut Babad Momana. #literasyikgalih #kilasdokumenter @galih.wib
textTranslated:
It is said that the Kota Gede cemetery is as complex as the Islamic Mataram palace. Located west of the Kota Gede Grand Mosque, this tomb is called Pasarean Hastana Kitha Ageng. This tomb complex consists of a mosque, a women's bathing spring which has a water source from the surrounding banyan trees and a men's bathing place as well as the graves of the founders of Mataram, namely Ki Ageng Pemanahan, Panembahan Senopati king I, founder of Mataram, Sultan Hamengkubuwono II, Pakualam I-IV and their relatives. The grave is included in the Sayangan Hamlet area, Jagalan, Banguntapan, Bantul Regency, Yogyakarta Special Region.
Inside there are also the Prbayaksa, Witana and Tajug wards. Entering the tomb you must wear traditional clothing. The atmosphere is quite shady and suitable for photo spots. This building, which still has a Hindu style in the middle of an Islamic kingdom, was built in 1589 according to the Babad Momana. #literasyikgalih #kilasdocumenter @galih.wib
title: Makam Raja-Raja Mataram Kotagede

name: Octavianus Pratama
text:
Makam Raja-raja Mataram adalah salah satu situs sejarah paling penting di Yogyakarta. Terletak di kawasan Kotagede,makam ini menjadi peristirahatan terakhir bagi para raja dan keluarga kerajaan Mataram Islam. Kompleks makam yang luas ini tidak hanya menyimpan nilai sejarah yang tinggi, tetapi juga menawarkan pengalaman spiritual yang mendalam.

Makam Raja-raja Mataram adalah bagian tak terpisahkan dari sejarah perkembangan Islam di Jawa. Kompleks makam ini mencerminkan kemegahan dan kekuasaan Kesultanan Mataram pada masanya. Bangunan-bangunan di kompleks makam ini menampilkan arsitektur Jawa yang khas dengan ornamen-ornamen yang indah. Setiap detailnya memiliki makna filosofis yang mendalam.

Secara keseluruhan, Makam Raja-raja Mataram adalah destinasi wisata sejarah dan religi yang wajib dikunjungi saat berada di Yogyakarta.Selain nilai sejarahnya yang tinggi, kompleks makam ini juga menawarkan keindahan arsitektur dan suasana yang tenang.

Disclaimer dan Saran untuk Pengunjung Makam Raja-raja Mataram  untuk ulasan saya tentang Makam Raja-raja Mataram berdasarkan pengalaman pribadi saya. Perlu diingat bahwa pendapat setiap pengunjung bisa berbeda-beda.

Semoga informasi ini membantu!
textTranslated:
The Tombs of the Mataram Kings is one of the most important historical sites in Yogyakarta. Located in the Kotagede area, this tomb is the final resting place for the kings and royal family of Islamic Mataram. This extensive tomb complex not only holds high historical value, but also offers a deep spiritual experience.

The tombs of the Mataram Kings are an inseparable part of the history of the development of Islam in Java. This tomb complex reflects the splendor and power of the Mataram Sultanate at that time. The buildings in this tomb complex display typical Javanese architecture with beautiful ornaments. Every detail has a deep philosophical meaning.

Overall, the Tombs of the Mataram Kings is a historical and religious tourist destination that must be visited while in Yogyakarta. Apart from its high historical value, this tomb complex also offers architectural beauty and a calm atmosphere.

Disclaimer and Suggestions for Visitors to the Tomb of the Mataram Kings for my review of the Tomb of the Mataram Kings based on my personal experience. Please remember that each visitor's opinion can be different.

Hope this information helps!

Wisata religi, sejarah, dan budaya jadi satu.

Bangunannya adalah perpaduan arsitektur Hindu dan Jawa-Islam, tidak ada ciri-ciri Arab ataupun Timur Tengah lainnya disini.

Parkir motor Rp 3.000, untuk masuk dan melihat-lihat dalamnya bayar seikhlasnya di pendopo, ada abdi dalem yang jaga.
Tapi, jika ingin berziarah ke makam para raja WAJIB menggunakan baju adat Jawa, khusus bagi perempuan WAJIB menggunakan kemben (buka jilbab).
Biaya sewa baju adat Rp 35.000
textTranslated:
Religious, historical and cultural tourism in one.
The aura is really shady, if the Kraton area and the main square have a classic and romantic vibe, then the vibe of Kotagede is ancient Jogja.

The building is a combination of Hindu and Javanese-Islamic architecture, there are no Arab or other Middle Eastern features here.

Motorbike parking Rp. 3,000, to enter and look inside, pay as willingly as possible at the pavilion, there is a courtier on guard.
However, if you want to make a pilgrimage to the tombs of the kings you MUST wear traditional Javanese clothes, especially for women you MUST wear a kemben (remove the hijab).
The cost to rent traditional clothes is IDR 35,000
title: Makam Raja-Raja Mataram Kotagede

name: Satriyo Wi
text: Sebagaimana namanya, kompleks makam Imogiri memang diperuntukkan sebagai tempat peristirahatan terakhir bagi raja-raja Mataram Islam dan raja-raja turunannya, hingga terbelahnya Dinasti Mataram menjadi dua kerajaan yang masih eksis hingga saat ini, yakni Kasunanan Surakarta dan Kesultanan Yogyakarta....  Bila berziarah ke tempat ini tidak lengkap rasanya bila tidak menikmati sebuah minuman wedang uwuh. Wedang uwuh merupakan sebuah minuman seduh yang terbuat dari campuran rempah-rempah seperti kayu manis, secang, gula batu dan juga daun cengkeh. Bila para peziarah lapar, dapat menikmati pecel yang lengkap dengan baceman dan kembang turi... terletak di imogiri bantul yogyakarta
textTranslated: As the name suggests, the Imogiri tomb complex was intended as the final resting place for the Islamic Mataram kings and their descendant kings, until the split of the Mataram dynasty into two kingdoms that still exist today, namely the Kasunanan of Surakarta and the Sultanate of Yogyakarta... When making a pilgrimage Going to this place is incomplete if you don't enjoy a wedang uwuh drink. Wedang uwuh is a brewed drink made from a mixture of spices such as cinnamon, secang, rock sugar and clove leaves. If pilgrims are hungry, they can enjoy pecel complete with baceman and turi flower... located in Imogiri Bantul, Yogyakarta

text: Makam Imogiri, adalah lokasi peristirahatan terakhir Raja-Raja Mataram dan keluarganya. Kompleks pemakaman ini terletak kurang lebih 16 km di sebelah selatan Keraton Yogyakarta, tepatnya di wilayah Desa Girirejo dan Desa Wukirsari, Kecamatan Imogiri, Kabupaten Bantul, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta.  Imogiri berasal dari kata hima dan giri. Hima berarti kabut dan giri berarti gunung, sehingga Imogiri bisa diartikan sebagai gunung yang diselimuti kabut.
textTranslated: Imogiri Tomb, is the final resting place of the Mataram Kings and their families. This burial complex is located approximately 16 km south of the Yogyakarta Palace, precisely in the area of ​​Girirejo Village and Wukirsari Village, Imogiri District, Bantul Regency, Yogyakarta Special Region.  Imogiri comes from the words hima and giri. Hima means fog and giri means mountain, so Imogiri can be interpreted as a mountain covered in fog.
title: Makam Raja-Raja Imogiri

address: 39HW+R83 Makam Raja-Raja Yogyakarta & Surakarta Pajimatan, Karang Kulon, Wukirsari, Kec. Imogiri, Kabupaten Bantul, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55782, Indonesia

Lokasinya bisa dijangkau 15 menit dari malioboro dengan jalan kaki. Bisa juga dijangkau dengan kendaraan pribadi, ojek online maupuj transjogja.
Ada foodcourt di lapangan depan Kraton, dengan area parkir yang luas baik untuk motor maupun mobil. Parkir motor sekitar Rp.2000.
Kraton Pakualaman sendiri terdiri dari dua area, yaitu area depan yang bisa dikunjungi wisatawan umum dan area khusus yang digunakan sebagai tempat tinggal keluarga Kraton.
textTranslated:
The location can be reached in 15 minutes from Malioboro on foot. It can also be reached by private vehicle, online motorbike taxi or Transjogja.
There is a food court in the front square of the Kraton, with a large parking area for both motorbikes and cars. Motorbike parking around Rp. 2000.
Pakualaman Palace itself consists of two areas, namely the front area which can be visited by general tourists and a special area which is used as a residence for the Kraton family.
title: Pura Pakualaman

name: Hartono Budi
text:
Kediaman KGPAA Paku Alam X, Wakil Gubernur DIY. Letaknya tidak jauh dari titik nol kilometer Yogyakarta, kurang lebih 1 KM arah timur seberang Sungai Code atau jembatan Sayidan. Tepatnya di Jalan Sultan Agung utara jalan.

Bersama-sama dengan Kasultanan Yogyakarta Kadipaten Paku Alaman bergabung dengan Negara Kesatuan Republik Indonesia. Menjadi daerah otonomi khusus setingkat provinsi, bernama Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta.

Jika berkunjung kesini disarankan tidak memakai sendal jepit, tiket masuk free hanya disediakan kotak donasi seikhlasnya. Penyambutan dan pelayanan pengunjung ramah dan santun, lingkungannya terawat asri.
textTranslated:
Residence of KGPAA Paku Alam X, Deputy Governor of DIY. It is located not far from the zero kilometer point of Yogyakarta, approximately 1 KM east across the Code River or the Sayidan bridge. Precisely on Jalan Sultan Agung north of the road.

Together with the Yogyakarta Sultanate, the Paku Alaman Duchy joined the Unitary State of the Republic of Indonesia. Became a special autonomous region at provincial level, named Yogyakarta Special Region.

If you visit here, it is recommended that you do not wear flip-flops, free entry tickets are provided, only a donation box is provided if you wish. The reception and service to visitors is friendly and polite, the environment is beautifully maintained.
title: Pura Pakualaman

address: 59CX+3HP, Jl. Masjid Besar Mataram, Sayangan, Jagalan, Banguntapan, Bantul Regency, Special Region of Yogyakarta 55192, Indonesia
name: Mas Pakem
text:
Tempat bersejarah, peninggalan leluhur budaya dan kearifan lokal.
Wajib di kunjungi terutama pengenalan bagi anak-anak, dan orang awam.

Makam raja-raja tidak seseram seperti makam pada umumnya.
Dibangun pada abad ke 16, tahun 1500an.
Terletak di kota gede, jarak tempuh dari pusat kota yogyakarta sekitar 8km.

Bisa berfoto-foto ditempat ini kecuali didalam makam. Bisa banget buat photoshoot dan prewedd, dengan bayar seikhlasnya.
Untuk memasuki area makam wajib menggunakan pakaian adat jawa, biaya sewa  Rp 30.000/baju.
Tempatnya asri bersih nyaman, damai, tentrem ayem.
textTranslated:
Historical places, cultural heritage and local wisdom.
A must visit, especially for introductions for children and lay people.

The tombs of kings are not as scary as tombs in general.
Built in the 16th century, 1500s.
Located in a big city, the distance from Yogyakarta city center is around 8km.

You can take photos in this place except in the tomb. You can really do photoshoots and pre-weddings, by paying as much as you like.
To enter the tomb area you must wear traditional Javanese clothing, rental fee IDR 30,000/clothing.
The place is beautiful, clean, comfortable, peaceful, peaceful and calm.
title: Makam Raja-Raja Mataram Kotagede

address: 59CX+3HP, Jl. Masjid Besar Mataram, Sayangan, Jagalan, Banguntapan, Bantul Regency, Special Region of Yogyakarta 55192, Indonesia

text: Salah satu lokasi ziarah yang menjadi pilihan utama pengunjung. Cocok untuk dijadikan tempat untuk belajar soal budaya setempat dan bisa berdiskusi langsung dengan abdi dalem. Untuk melakukan ziarah makam, harus mengenakan pakaian adat Jawa yang disewakan kepada peziarah. Oiya, juga terdapat sumur untuk mengambil air berkat dan tidak dikenakan biaya.
textTranslated: One of the pilgrimage locations that is the main choice for visitors. Suitable as a place to learn about local culture and be able to discuss directly with courtiers. To make a grave pilgrimage, you must wear traditional Javanese clothing which is rented to pilgrims. Oh yes, there is also a well to collect blessed water and there is no charge.
title: Makam Raja-Raja Mataram Kotagede

address: 59CX+3HP, Jl. Masjid Besar Mataram, Sayangan, Jagalan, Banguntapan, Bantul Regency, Special Region of Yogyakarta 55192, Indonesia
name: Fauzi Anggoro
text: Kompleks makam raja Kotagede. Salah satu wisata yang enak banget buat ditelusurin. Kompleks perkampungan yang terdapat kompleks masjid Kauman yang bersebelahan dengan makam raja-raja Mataram Islam. Disini disajikan bangunan hasil persilangan kebudayaan antara Hindu dengan Islam. Di luar kompleks masjid Kauman, ada lorong-lorong perkampungan yang menyajikan suasana tradisional. Banyak spot foto keren dan tentunya kehangatan warga di kampung ini bikin suasana nyaman kita Jogja bisa terasa.
textTranslated: Kotagede king's tomb complex. One of the tourist attractions that is really fun to explore. The village complex contains the Kauman mosque complex which is adjacent to the tombs of the Islamic Mataram kings. Here, buildings are presented as a result of the cultural cross between Hinduism and Islam. Outside the Kauman mosque complex, there are village alleys that provide a traditional atmosphere. There are lots of cool photo spots and of course the warmth of the people in this village makes Jogja feel comfortable.
title: Makam Raja-Raja Mataram Kotagede

salah satu masjid  tertua di Yogyakarta. Bangunan ini merupakan masjid peninggalan Mataram yang masih bisa dilihat sekarang dan juga masih dipakai sebagaimana fungsinya .Di kotagede Yogyakarta memang terdapat banyak peninggalan bersejarah yang menyimpan informasi pada masa kerajaan Mataram. Salah satu tempat bersejarah di kota ini adalah Masjid Agung Kotagede yang dibangun pada zaman kerajaan Mataram pada tahun 1640 oleh Sultan Agung bergotong-royong dengan masyarakat setempat yang pada umumnya waktu itu beragama Hindu dan Budha.

Melangkah memasuki halaman Masjid akan didapati sebuag pohon beringin tua yang umurnya sudah ratusan tahun yang bernama Wringin Sepuh, Pohon tersebut oleh masyarakat sekitar dianggap keramat dan diyakini membawa berkah bagi siapa saja yang mau bertapa di bawah pohon tersebut. Disekitar pohon tersebut terdapat parit yang mengelilingi Masjid. Parit tersebut dahulu dipakai untuk tempat berwudhu tetapi sekarang dipergunakan sebagai tambak.

Masjid Kotagede Yogyakarta yang sudah berusia ratusan tahun memiliki sebuah prasasti yang menyebutkan bahwa Masjid tersebut dibuat dalam dua tahap. Tahap pertama dibangun pada masa Sultan Agung yang berhasil membangun inti masjid yang berukuran kecil yang disebut langgar. Tahap kedua masjid ini dibangun oleh Raja Kasunanan Surakarta, Paku Buwono X. Ada perbedaan pada bangunan masjid tersebut yang dibangun oleh Sultan Agung dan Paku Buwono X pada tiangnya. Tiang masjid yang dibangun Sultan Agung berasal dari kayu, sedangkan tiang yang dibangun oleh Paku Buwono X berbahan dari besi.

Masjid ini sampai saat ini tetap dipakai untuk tempat beribadah umat Islam warga setempat. Bangunan tersebut merupakan bentuk toleransi antara umat beragama waktu itu. Sebagian besar waktu itu warga masih memeluk agama Hindu dan Budha dan dengan senang hati ikut membantu pembangunan masjid ttersebut. Ciri khas Hindu dan Budha terlihat dari tiang dari kayu yang dibangun pada masa pemerintahan Sultan Agung yaitu gapura masjid yang berbentuk Paduraksa.

Bangunan masjid tersebut berbentuk limasan yang dapat dilihat dari atapnya yang bebentuk limas dan ruangan terbagi menjadi dua, yaitu inti dan serambi. Masjid ini terdapat sebuah bedug yang berusia cukup tua yang dahulu merupakan hadiah dari Nyai Pringgit dan sampai sekarang bedug tersebut masih dipakai sebagai penanda waktu untuk berdoa.
textTranslated:
one of the oldest mosques in Yogyakarta. This building is a mosque inherited from Mataram which can still be seen today and is still used for its function. In Kotagede Yogyakarta there are many historical relics that contain information from the time of the Mataram kingdom. One of the historical places in this city is the Kotagede Grand Mosque which was built during the Mataram kingdom era in 1640 by Sultan Agung in collaboration with the local community, who were generally Hindu and Buddhist at that time.

Stepping into the courtyard of the mosque you will find an old banyan tree that is hundreds of years old called Wringin Sepuh. This tree is considered sacred by the local community and is believed to bring blessings to anyone who wants to meditate under the tree. Around the tree there is a ditch that surrounds the mosque. The ditch was previously used as a place for ablution but is now used as a pond.

The Kotagede Yogyakarta Mosque, which is hundreds of years old, has an inscription which states that the mosque was built in two stages. The first stage was built during the time of Sultan Agung who succeeded in building a small mosque core called langgar. The second phase of this mosque was built by the King of Kasunanan Surakarta, Paku Buwono X. There are differences in the mosque building which was built by Sultan Agung and Paku Buwono The pillars of the mosque built by Sultan Agung were made of wood, while the pillars built by Paku Buwono X were made of iron.

This mosque is still used as a place of worship for local Muslims. This building was a form of tolerance between religious communities at that time. Most of the residents at that time still embraced Hinduism and Buddhism and were happy to help build the mosque. Typical Hindu and Buddhist characteristics can be seen from the wooden pillars built during the reign of Sultan Agung, namely the mosque gate in the shape of Paduraksa.

The mosque building is pyramid-shaped which can be seen from the pyramid-shaped roof and the room is divided into two, namely the core and the foyer. This mosque has a fairly old drum which was once a gift from Nyai Pringgit and to this day the drum is still used to mark the time for prayer.
title: Makam Raja-Raja Mataram Kotagede

text:
KOTAGEDE sering disebut sebagai kota perak, karena di wilayah tersebut diproduksi kerajinan perak yang berkualitas dan bervariasi.

Selain itu juga dikenal sebagai kota bekas pusat pemerintahan kerajaan Mataram Islam di wilayah Yogyakarta.

Suasana bekas ibukota kerajaan masih terlihat kental. Di komplek ini banyak dijumpai peninggalan sejarah yang sangat berharga, misalnya Masjid Agung Kotagede yang merupakan masjid paling tua di Yogyakarta dan makam raja-raja Mataram serta tokoh-tokoh pendiri Kerajaan Mataram antara lain Panembahan Senopati beserta keluarganya.

Di bagian Selatan terdapat pemandian dengan sumber mata air yang berasal dari komplek makam, namanya Sendang Kakung dan Sendang Putri, yang hingga kini masih dipercaya bisa membuat awet muda bagi siapa saja yang mencuci muka menggunakan air sendang tersebut.
textTranslated:
KOTAGEDE is often referred to as the city of silver, because the area produces quality and varied silver crafts.

Apart from that, it is also known as the former government center of the Islamic Mataram Kingdom in the Yogyakarta region.

The atmosphere of the former royal capital still looks strong. In this complex you can find many valuable historical remains, for example the Kotagede Great Mosque which is the oldest mosque in Yogyakarta and the tombs of the Mataram kings and the founding figures of the Mataram Kingdom, including Panembahan Senopati and his family.

In the southern part there are baths with spring water originating from the tomb complex, called Sendang Kakung and Sendang Putri, which are still believed to make anyone who washes their face using spring water stay young.
title: Makam Raja-Raja Mataram Kotagede

name: Azis abdul Rohman
text:
Sunan Muria adalah Ulama yang termasuk dalam anggota dewan Wali Songo. Nama lahirnya adalah Umar Said. Ia adalah putra Sunan Kalijaga dan Dewi Saroh binti Maulana Ishaq.
Nama Sunan Muria sendiri diperkirakan berasal dari nama gunung (Gunung Muria), yang terletak di sebelah utara kota Kudus, Jawa Tengah, tempat Sunan Muria dimakamkan. Sunan Muria wafat pada tahun 1560 M.

Sunan Muria menikah dengan Dewi Sujinah putri Sunan Ngudung, adik dari Sunan Kudus dan Sunan Muria menikah dengan dewi Roroyono Putri Ki Ageng Ngerang dan Nyai Ageng Ngerang.[3] Sunan Muria menikah dengan dewi sujinah dikaruniai seorang anak bernama Raden Saridin,Syech Jangkung/Waliyullah Sunan Landoh.

Sedangkan, pernikahan Sunan Muria dengan dewi Roroyono Putri Ki Ageng Ngerang dan Nyai Ageng Ngerang dikaruniai tiga orang anak sunan nyamplungan, raden ayu nasiki,pangeran santri, Salah satu putra Sunan Muria yang terkenal ialah (Panembahan Pangulu) Pangeran Jogodipo , yang makamnya berada satu kompleks di Colo.

Sumber versi catatan sejarah menyebutkan asal usul Sunan Muria sebagai anak kandung dari sunan ngudung/sunan mandalika sangat tidak sesuai karena bukti kebenaran otentik dewi sujinah istri sunan muria adalah putri dari Sunan Ngudung "Raden Usman Haji" bin As-Sayyid Ali Murtadho Sunan Gisik kakak sunan ampel
textTranslated:
Sunan Muria is a Ulama who is a member of the Wali Songo council. His birth name was Umar Said. He is the son of Sunan Kalijaga and Dewi Saroh bint Maulana Ishaq.
The name Sunan Muria itself is thought to come from the name of the mountain (Mount Muria), which is located to the north of the city of Kudus, Central Java, where Sunan Muria is buried. Sunan Muria died in 1560 AD.

Sunan Muria married Dewi Sujinah daughter of Sunan Ngudung, sister of Sunan Kudus and Sunan Muria married goddess Roroyono Putri Ki Ageng Ngerang and Nyai Ageng Ngerang.[3] Sunan Muria married the goddess Sujinah and was blessed with a child named Raden Saridin, Syech Jangkung/Waliyullah Sunan Landoh.

Meanwhile, Sunan Muria's marriage to the goddess Roroyono Putri Ki Ageng Ngerang and Nyai Ageng Ngerang was blessed with three children Sunan Nyamplungan, Raden Ayu Nasiki, prince of santri. One of Sunan Muria's famous sons is (Panembahan Pangulu) Prince Jogodipo, whose grave is in the same complex. in Colo.

The source version of historical records stating that the origin of Sunan Muria as the biological son of Sunan Ngudung/Sunan Mandalika is very inconsistent because the authentic evidence of the goddess Sujinah, Sunan Muria's wife, is the daughter of Sunan Ngudung "Raden Usman Haji" bin As-Sayyid Ali Murtadho Sunan Gisik Sunan's older brother ampel

name: MUH JUNAEDI
text:
Makam Sunan Muria merupakan salah satu bukti arkeologis yang berkenaan dengan masa awal perkembangan Islam di Jawa khusunya di wilayah Kudus, Pati dan sekitarnya. Kompleks Makam Sunan Muria berada di Bukit Muria yang terletak di Desa Colo, Kecamatan Dawe, Kabupaten Kudus, Provinsi Jawa Tengah dan berada pada ketinggian lebih dari 1600 meter di atas permukaan laut.

Sunan Muria adalah salah seorang peyebar Islam di Jawa yang tergabung dalam kelompok Wali Songo. Wilayah dakwah Sunan Muria meliputi Kudus, Pati dan sekitarnya terutama di daerah-daerah pedalaman seputar Gunung Muria. Menurut latar belakang sejarah, ada beberapa versi mengenai silsilah Sunan Muria. Versi pertama menyebutkan bahwa Sunan Muria mempunyai nama kecil R. Umar Said yang merupakan anak Sunan Kalijaga dari istrinya yang bernama Dewi Saroh putri Maulana Ishak. Sunan Muria menikah dengan Sujinah anak dari Sunan Ngudung (R. Usman Haji). Menurut cerita versi pertama ini, Sunan Muria memiliki hubungan kekerabatan dengan Sunan Kudus (Jafar Shadiq), yaitu saudara ipar karena Sunan Kudus adalah kakak Dewi Sujinah istri Sunan Muria.

Adapun versi kedua mengatakan bahwa Sunan Muria adalah putra Sunan Ngudung dari istrinya yang bernama Dewi Sarifah. Putra Sunan Ngudung lainnya antara lain Sunan Giri II, Sunan Kudus, dan Sunan Giri III. Sedangkan hubungannya dengan Sunan Kalijaga adalah Sunan Kalijaga merupakan putra Tumenggung Wilatikta, Putra Ario Tejo III, Putra R. Penanggungan. Sedangkan Sunan Ngudung adalah putra Dewi Maduretno, putra R. Baribin, putra R. Penanggungan. Jadi menurut versi ini Sunan Muria adalah keponakan jauh Sunan Kalijaga.

Metode dakwah yang digunakan Sunan Muria dengan cara yang bijaksana dalam menghadapi masyarakat yang menjadi objek dakwahnya. Dakwah yang dilakukan Sunan Muria diselaraskan dengan keperayaan lama, adat yang bertentangan dengan ajaran Islam dilakukan dengan perlahan-lahan. Sunan Muria juga dikenal berdakwah melalui kesenian. Salah satu tembang macapat hasil ciptaannya adalah Sinom dan Kinanti.

Kompleks Makam Sunan Muria merupakan salah satu living monument yang sampai saat ini masih ramai dikunjungi oleh para peziarah. Dalam kompleks Makam Sunan Muria, selain makam juga terdapat bangunan masjid.

Kemendikbud
textTranslated:
Sunan Muria's tomb is one of the archaeological evidence relating to the early development of Islam in Java, especially in the Kudus, Pati and surrounding areas. The Sunan Muria Tomb Complex is on Muria Hill which is located in Colo Village, Dawe District, Kudus Regency, Central Java Province and is at an altitude of more than 1600 meters above sea level.

Sunan Muria was one of the spreaders of Islam in Java who was part of the Wali Songo group. Sunan Muria's preaching area included Kudus, Pati and its surroundings, especially in the inland areas around Mount Muria. According to historical background, there are several versions regarding Sunan Muria's genealogy. The first version states that Sunan Muria had the nickname R. Umar Said, who was Sunan Kalijaga's son from his wife, Dewi Saroh, daughter of Maulana Ishak. Sunan Muria married Sujinah, daughter of Sunan Ngudung (R. Usman Haji). According to this first version of the story, Sunan Muria is related to Sunan Kudus (Jafar Sadiq), namely his brother-in-law because Sunan Kudus is the older brother of Dewi Sujinah, Sunan Muria's wife.

The second version says that Sunan Muria is the son of Sunan Ngudung from his wife, Dewi Sarifah. Sunan Ngudung's other sons include Sunan Giri II, Sunan Kudus, and Sunan Giri III. Meanwhile, his relationship with Sunan Kalijaga is that Sunan Kalijaga is the son of Tumenggung Wilatikta, Putra Ario Tejo III, Putra R. Penanggungan. Meanwhile, Sunan Ngudung is the son of Dewi Maduretno, son of R. Baribin, son of R. Penanggungan. So according to this version Sunan Muria is Sunan Kalijaga's distant nephew.

The da'wah method used by Sunan Muria was wise in dealing with the people who were the object of his da'wah. The preaching carried out by Sunan Muria was aligned with old celebrations, customs which were contrary to Islamic teachings were carried out slowly. Sunan Muria is also known for preaching through art. One of the macapat songs he created is Sinom and Kinanti.

The Sunan Muria Tomb Complex is one of the living monuments which is still busy with pilgrims. In the Sunan Muria Tomb complex, apart from the tomb, there is also a mosque building.

Ministry of Education and Culture
