name: Yustina Andryastuti
text: Perkembangan dan penyebaran islam di pulau jawa tak lepas dari peran wali songo, salah satunya adalah Sunan Muria. Mempunyai nama asli Umar Said beliau berdakwah sekitar abad 15 melalui pendekatan budaya jawa di kalangan masyarakat yang tinggal di Kudus, Jepara dan sekitarnya. Saat ini makam beliau yang terletak di Gunung Muria dengan ketinggian sekitar 1600 mdpl masih begitu sarat peziarah yang datang berkunjung. Untuk mencapai lokasi masjid serta makam Sunan Muria bisa di akses melalui Desa Colo, Kudus naik ke arah Muria. Setelah tiba di pelataran parkir yg sudah di siapkan, pengunjung beralih ke moda transportasi ojek khusus muria berbayar 20K skali jalan. Memang saat ini pilihan untuk mencapai lokasi komplek Sunan Muria (demikian juga saat kembali menuju lokasi parkir) akan lebih baik dicapai menggunakan ojek khusus yang sudah menguasai medan karena jarak yang agak jauh dari parkiran kendaraan dan jalanan menanjak begitu curam serta berliku tajam saking tinggi nya hingga sedikit memacu adrenalin tapi mempunyai view yang indah dengan udara sejuk nan berhembus.
textTranslated: The development and spread of Islam on the island of Java cannot be separated from the role of Songo saints, one of whom was Sunan Muria. With the real name Umar Said, he preached around the 15th century using a Javanese cultural approach among the people living in Kudus, Jepara and surrounding areas. Currently, his grave, which is located on Mount Muria at an altitude of around 1600 meters above sea level, is still full of pilgrims who come to visit. To reach the location of the mosque and Sunan Muria's grave, you can access it via Colo Village, Kudus and go up towards Muria. After arriving at the parking lot that has been prepared, visitors switch to the special Muria motorbike taxi transportation mode which costs 20K one way. Indeed, currently the option to reach the location of the Sunan Muria complex (as well as when returning to the parking location) would be better achieved using a special motorbike taxi that has mastered the terrain because the distance is quite far from the vehicle parking lot and the road climbs very steeply and turns sharply so high that a bit of an adrenaline rush but has a beautiful view with cool, blowing air.
title: Tomb of Sunan Muria

text:
Tempatnya di ketinggian dgn suasana tenang dan sejuk.  Saya kemarin  jam 7 pagi sdh sampai sana. Agar bisa sekaligus ke makam Sunan Kudus dan makam Sunan Kalijaga(Demak).
Lanjut ya..
Dari tempat parkir kendaraan kita bisa jalan kaki atau naik ojek. Saya pilih naik ojek. Tips seblm naik ojek:
- bagi yg pakai jilbab akan lebih baik pakai jilbab instan
- bawa tas slempang atau tas punggung agar tangan bisa pegangan
- jangan pegang hp krn bs jatuh di jalan
- siapkan uang 20 rb utk sekali jalan
- ijin bang ojek utk pegangan
- bawa tas kresek buat tempat sandal/sepatu
Ojeknya ngebut banget. Mungkin agar kuat nanjak dengan  jalan yg sempit, dan berkelok.
Sampai atas kita turun kmd jalan kaki naik tangga. Pertama saya menuju ke masjid. Di sana suasana tenang, sejuk shg bs sholat dan berdoa dengan khusuk. Hbs sholat saya sempat merenung bagaimana jaman dulu perjuangan Sunan Muria berdakwah naik turun tempat setinggi itu utk menyebarkan agama islam.
Selesai sholat saya menuju ke makam. Sempat antri sekitar 20 menit.
Ohya siapkan uang utk sedekah krn ada bbrp kotak utk kita sedekah. Masuk makam kita bisa menyaksikan makam Sunan Muria dengan selambu putih. Selesai mendoakan beliau, saya pulang. Yg beda di tempat ini, sepanjang jalan banyak dijual buah parijotho yg katanya baik utk kandungan, juga pisang rebus yg panjang2. Hrgnya 15 rb isi 3. Pisangnya enak saya suka.
Plg saya naik ojek lagi. Kali ini lebih ektrem krn jalan turun. Badan rasanya mau mlorot terus. Akhirnya sampai juga kami kembali di tempat parkir. Jangan lupa sempatkan makan nasi pecel pakis di Warung Pojok bu Min.
MasyaAlloh enak luar biasa. Sayur pakisnya ijo, empuk, bumbu pecelnya sedep, ditambah peyek udang. Mantap banget deh...4 jempol. Bisa juga lauk telur ceplok, atau dadar. Sambil nyruput kopi item...
Bukan jam 8 nan sampai jam 3 sore.
textTranslated:
The place is at an altitude with a calm and cool atmosphere.  I arrived there yesterday at 7 am. So you can go to the tomb of Sunan Kudus and the tomb of Sunan Kalijaga (Demak) at the same time.
Continue okay..
From the vehicle parking area we can walk or take a motorbike taxi. I chose to take a motorbike taxi. Tips before riding a motorbike taxi:
- For those who wear the hijab, it would be better to wear an instant hijab
- bring a sling bag or backpack so your hands can hold it
- Don't hold your cellphone because it could fall on the road
- prepare 20 thousand for one trip
- permission from the motorbike taxi to handle it
- bring a plastic bag for sandals/shoes
The motorbike taxi was very fast. Maybe to be strong enough to climb up narrow, winding roads.
When we get to the top we go down then walk up the stairs. First I headed to the mosque. There the atmosphere is calm, cool so you can pray and pray fervently. After praying, I had time to reflect on how in the past Sunan Muria struggled to preach up and down high places to spread the religion of Islam.
After praying I went to the tomb. Had to queue for about 20 minutes.
Oh yes, prepare money for alms because there are several boxes for us to alms. Entering the tomb we can see Sunan Muria's grave with a white veil. After praying for him, I went home. What's different about this place is that along the road there are lots of parijotho fruit for sale which is said to be good for the womb, as well as long boiled bananas. The price is 15 thousand for 3. The bananas are delicious, I like them.
I'll take a motorbike taxi again. This time it was more extreme because the road went down. My body feels like it's going to keep sagging. Finally we arrived back at the parking lot. Don't forget to take the time to eat pecel fern rice at Warung Pojok Bu Min.
MashaAllah it's amazingly delicious. The fern vegetables are green, tender, the pecel seasoning is delicious, plus prawn shreds. It's really great...4 thumbs up. It can also be a side dish with fried eggs or omelet. While sipping coffee...
Not 8am to 3pm.

textTranslated: The tomb of Sheikh Maulana Magribi Wonobodro Blado Batang is the guardian's memorial. Here the pilgrimage is usually held on Mulan Suro on the 13th of Suro. Many visitors from outside the area, even from East Java, come here, it has become a local custom. Many traders and visitors come during the month of Suro, although in other months, many pilgrims come here to pray for the saint. The journey is quite congested to get to the Waliyullah's grave, but many people still come even though it rains. But now the local village government has made alternative routes or roads so that there are many roads to the tomb so it's not as crowded as before.

address: Pasarean, Pesarean, Adiwerna, Tegal Regency, Central Java 52194, Indonesia
name: Aswin G Sharif
text:
Sebuah tempat yang menggambarkan sisi gelap sejarah kerajaan Mataram. Raja Jawa Amangkurat I dikenal haus darah dan kekuasaan. Tidak segan menghabisi nyawa rakyatnya yang dianggap beroposisi, bahkan panglina perangnya sendiri yang setia dia perintahkan kpd pasukannya untuk dibunuh dengan seluruh anggota keluarganya. Kebiadabannya semakin menjadi-jadi manakala beliau pindah ke istana yang baru, sehingga akhirnya timbul pemberontakan dari dalam dan Mataram akhirnya jatuh ke tangan Raden Trunojoyo dari Madura. Amangkurat sempat meloloskan diri ke Imogiri, bermaksud membangun kembali kekuasaan namun gagal.
Makam raja ini tidak layak diziarahi. Tempat matinya orang orang zalim adalah tempat terkutuk sebagaimana kota al Ula yang dilarang untuk dikunjungi. Hindari menziarahi makam ini bila tidak ingin mendapatkan musibah, keberadaannya hanya untuk renungan dan pengingat catatan kelam  sejarah pra-Indonesia.
textTranslated:
A place that depicts the dark side of the history of the Mataram kingdom. Javanese King Amangkurat I was known to be thirsty for blood and power. He did not hesitate to end the lives of his people who were considered to be in opposition, even his own loyal warlord ordered his troops to be killed along with all members of his family. His savagery became even more intense when he moved to a new palace, so that finally a rebellion emerged from within and Mataram finally fell into the hands of Raden Trunojoyo from Madura. Amangkurat managed to escape to Imogiri, intending to reestablish power but failed.
The tomb of this king is not worth visiting. The place where unjust people die is a cursed place like the city of al Ula which is forbidden to visit. Avoid visiting this tomb if you don't want misfortune, its existence is only for reflection and a reminder of the dark records of pre-Indonesian history.
title: Situs Makam Sunan Amangkurat Agung

text: Benar-benar serasa masuk ke era 1900-an. Tempat terawat, tetapi ada beberapa bagian yg kurang terawat maksimal, contoh makam ibu R.A Kardinah yg berdebu. Secara umum bersih tertata. Tetapi sungguh sngat disayangkan banyaknya pengemis dewasa dan anak-anak, sangat disayangkan banget pengemis anak-anak, sudah trbiasa minta-minta sejak dini. Saya kira itu sangat tidak diharapkan oleh para leluhur yang dimakamkan di sini.
textTranslated: It really feels like you have stepped into the 1900s. The place is well maintained, but there are some parts that are not well maintained, for example the dusty grave of R.A Kardinah's mother. In general, clean and tidy. But it's really unfortunate that there are so many adult and child beggars, it's really unfortunate that child beggars have been used to begging from an early age. I guess that was very unexpected for the ancestors buried here.
title: Situs Makam Sunan Amangkurat Agung

Bingung?

Silahkan baca cerita rakyat tentang Amangkurat 1 yang dimakamkan di Tegal Arum.....

The fragrant aroma was immediately felt as it entered the grave area. We were lucky to be able to enter the tomb building. We met a tomb guard in his 90s who said he still had to cut the nails and hair of the late Sultan who had been dead for more than 200 years.

Confused?

Please read the folklore about Amangkurat 1 who was buried in Tegal Arum.....

text: Sebuah situs sejarah Kesultanan Mataram di tanah Tegal. Di sini dimakamkan raja Mataram keempat, Susuhunan Prabu Amangkurat I Agung, putra Sultan Agung Anyakrakusuma, yang wafat dalam pelariannya ke Batavia setelah ibukota Mataram di Plered jatuh ke tangan Trunajaya. Tempatnya terawat (masih dirawat oleh Keraton Surakarta) dan bersih.
textTranslated: A historical site of the Mataram Sultanate in Tegal. Here is buried the fourth king of Mataram, Susuhunan Prabu Amangkurat I Agung, son of Sultan Agung Anyakrakusuma, who died while fleeing to Batavia after the capital of Mataram in Plered fell into the hands of Trunajaya. The place is well maintained (still maintained by the Surakarta Palace) and clean.

address: Jl. Masjid No.46, Gunungketur, Pakualaman, Kota Yogyakarta, Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta 55166, Indonesia
name: Kusumo Wardoyo Cahyo Nugroho
text: Puro Paku Alaman (bahasa Jawa: Hanacaraka, ꦦꦸꦫꦦꦑꦸꦲꦭꦩ꧀ꦩꦟ꧀ , Purå Pakualaman) adalah bekas Istana kecil Kadipaten Paku Alaman. Istana ini menjadi tempat tinggal resmi para Pangeran Paku Alam mulai tahun 1813 sampai dengan tahun 1950, ketika pemerintah Negara Bagian Republik Indonesia menjadikan Kadipaten Paku Alaman (bersama-sama Kesultanan Yogyakarta) sebagai sebuah daerah berotonomi khusus setingkat provinsi yang bernama Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta . Ketika ingin berkunjung disuruh mengisi Buku tamu,  kemudian abdi dalem mengantar keliling istana. Perlu keseriusan pemerintah untuk merawat cagar budaya.
textTranslated: Puro Paku Alaman (Javanese: Hanacaraka, ꦦꦸꦫꦦꦑꦸꦲꦭꦩ꧀ꦩꦟ꧀ , Purå Pakualaman) is a former small palace of the Duchy of Paku Alaman. This palace was the official residence of the Princes of Paku Alam from 1813 until 1950, when the government of the Republic of Indonesia made the Duchy of Paku Alaman (together with the Sultanate of Yogyakarta) a special provincial-level autonomous region called Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta . When you want to visit, you are asked to fill in the guest book, then the courtiers take you around the palace. The government needs to be serious about maintaining cultural heritage.
title: Pura Pakualaman

address: 8VMX+FHJ, jl terminal wisata, Colo, Kec. Dawe, Kabupaten Kudus, Jawa Tengah 59353, Indonesia
name: Eko Pujiono
text:
Sudah dibuka kembali bagi para peziarah sejak awal Agustus 2020. Lokasi dapat dijangkau dengan mudah. Bagi peziarah yang menggunakan kendaraan umum, turun di Terminal Colo. Kumudian dapat melanjutkan perjalanan dengan berjalan kaki atau naik ojek. Tukang ojek mudah dikenali dengan seragam yang dikenakannya. Ongkosnya sekitar sepuluh sampai dua puluh ribu untuk sekali jalan. Bagi yang menggunakan sepeda motor, dapat menitipkannya di tempat penitipan yang tersedia. Biaya titip sekaligus parkir adalah lima ribu rupiah. Kemudian bisa melanjutkan berjalan kaki atau ngojek.

Oh, ya, sebelum Terminal Colo terdapat loket pintu masuk kawasan wisata religi Colo. HTM-nya murah meriah kok.

Jika Anda memilih berjalan kaki, maka perlu persiapkan fisik terlebih dahulu. Disarankan melakukan pemanasan ringan agar terhindar dari kram otot saat menaiki ratusan anak tangga menuju area masjid dan makam. Mengenai jumlah anak tangga, ada yang menyebut mencapai seribu lebih. Saat menapaki anak tangga perlu berhati-hati. Ada batu-batu yang licin. Jika capek bisa beristirahat dulu sambil berbelanja. Kanan-kirinya merupakan kios-kios penjual makanan, minuman, mainan, pakaian, dan berbagai buah tangan lainnya. Bahkan sejak di depan gapura pintu masuk sudah ada banyak penjual yang menawarkan jajaannya.

Setibanya di komplek masjid dan makam R. Umar Said atau Sunan Kudus, udara sejuk semakin terasa merasuk. Dipersilahkan melakukan aktivitas di masjid atau makam. Terdapat petunjuk yang cukup dan jelas untuk membantu para peziarah.

Oh, ya, bagi para pengunjung dan peziarah diwajibkan mematuhi protokol kesehatan. Terutama dalam menggunakan masker dan mencuci tangan. Di area wudhu tersedia sabun cair dalam kemasan botol. Petugas juga akan mengecek suhu tubuh peziarah menggunakan thermogun. Harap tidak berdesakan dan selalu mematuhi arahan para petugas.

Oh, ya, area makam terdapat di sebelah barat masjid. Di sini juga tersedia sumber air peninggalan Sang Sunan. Air ini dipercaya memiliki banyak khasiat, terutama menghilangkan dahaga setelah menaiki ratusan anak tangga. Mengenai manfaat khusus lainnya, itu bergantung kepada pihak yang memercayai.

Yang terpenting senantiasa tertib dan menjaga kebersihan lingkungan dengan membuang sampah di tempat yang disedikan. Satu lagi, jaga adab atawa sopan santun saat berada di sini ya.

Selamat berziarah bagi kalian.
textTranslated:
It has been reopened for pilgrims since early August 2020. The location can be reached easily. For pilgrims using public transportation, get off at Colo Terminal. Then you can continue your journey on foot or by motorbike taxi. Motorbike taxi drivers are easily recognized by the uniforms they wear. The fare is around ten to twenty thousand for one way. For those who use motorbikes, they can leave them in the storage area provided. The deposit and parking fee is five thousand rupiah. Then you can continue walking or riding a motorbike taxi.

Oh, yes, before the Colo Terminal there is a counter at the entrance to the Colo religious tourism area. The HTM is really cheap.

If you choose to walk, you need to prepare physically first. It is recommended to do a light warm-up to avoid muscle cramps when climbing hundreds of stairs to the mosque and tomb area. Regarding the number of stairs, some say it reaches more than a thousand. When climbing stairs you need to be careful. There are slippery rocks. If you are tired, you can rest first while shopping. Right and left are stalls selling food, drinks, toys, clothes and various other souvenirs. Even in front of the entrance gate, there are already many sellers offering their wares.

When we arrived at the mosque complex and the grave of R. Umar Said or Sunan Kudus, the cool air was increasingly pervasive. You are welcome to carry out activities at mosques or cemeteries. There are sufficient and clear instructions to help pilgrims.

Oh, yes, visitors and pilgrims are required to comply with health protocols. Especially in using masks and washing hands. In the ablution area, liquid soap is available in bottles. Officers will also check the body temperature of pilgrims using a thermogun. Please do not crowd and always obey the officers' directions.

Oh, yes, the grave area is to the west of the mosque. Here there is also a water source left by Sang Sunan. This water is believed to have many benefits, especially quenching thirst after climbing hundreds of stairs. Regarding other specific benefits, it depends on the trusting party.

The most important thing is to always be orderly and keep the environment clean by throwing away rubbish in the places provided. One more thing, maintain your manners or manners when you are here.

Happy pilgrimage to you.
title: Tomb of Sunan Muria

address: 8VMX+FHJ, jl terminal wisata, Colo, Kec. Dawe, Kabupaten Kudus, Jawa Tengah 59353, Indonesia
name: Sugeng Dwi Budi
text:
Raden Umar Said atau Sunan Muria merupakan salah satu anggota walisongo yang berperan penting dalam penyebaran agama Islam, khususnya di gunung Muria, Jawa Tengah. Beliau merupakan putera Sunan Kalijaga dan terkenal akan ilmunya yang sakti. Selain itu, beliau juga terkenal sebagai pencipta tembang Sinom dan Kinanthi. Dalam melaksanakan dakwahnya, Sunan Muria lebih menekankan pada kaum nelayan, pedagang, dan rakyat jelata.

Sunan Muria merupakan putera dari Sunan Kalijaga melalui pernikahannya bersama Dewi Saroh, yang merupakan puteri dari Syekh Maulana Ishak, seorang ulama terkenal di Samudra Pasai Aceh. Dengan demikian maka Sunan Muria masih merupakan keponakan dari Sunan Giri. Saat masih kecil, Sunan Muria memiliki nama Raden Prawoto. Selain itu, beliau juga sering dipanggil dengan Raden Umar Said atau Raden Umar Syahid.
textTranslated:
Raden Umar Said or Sunan Muria was a member of the walisongo who played an important role in the spread of Islam, especially on Mount Muria, Central Java. He was the son of Sunan Kalijaga and was famous for his powerful knowledge. Apart from that, he is also famous as the creator of the songs Sinom and Kinanthi. In carrying out his preaching, Sunan Muria placed greater emphasis on fishermen, traders and common people.

Sunan Muria is the son of Sunan Kalijaga through his marriage to Dewi Saroh, who is the daughter of Sheikh Maulana Ishak, a famous cleric in Samudra Pasai Aceh. Thus, Sunan Muria is still the nephew of Sunan Giri. When he was little, Sunan Muria had the name Raden Prawoto. Apart from that, he is also often called Raden Umar Said or Raden Umar Syahid.
title: Tomb of Sunan Muria

textTranslated: Sunan Muria named Sheikh Raden Umar Said is a descendant of Sunan Kalijaga with a mother named Dewi Sarah daughter of Sunan Gresik.. Sunan Muria's name is attributed to Mount Muria where he lived... Just like other saints he prefers to be alone meditating in a quiet place .. he preached following the way his parents preached, preaching by inserting Javanese culture with the aim of getting closer to the Javanese community which at that time was majority Hindu.

text:
Makam Sunan Muria terletak di lereng Gunung Muria di Kabupaten Kudus Jawa Tengah atau tepatnya beralamat di Desa Colo Kecamatan Dawe Kab. Kudus. Di sekitar makamnya, ada 17 makam prajurit dan abdi dalem yang dipercaya sebagai pengawalnya.

Makam Sunan Muria tidak seperti makam para wali lainnya, makam ini terletak di ketinggian 1600 mdpl tepatnya di lereng Muria yang terletak di Desa Colo, Kudus, Jawa Tengah. Untuk menuju makam Sunan Muria cukup melakukan perjalanan ke Kudus. Sebelum masjid Menara Kudus terdapat petunjuk jalan menuju Makam Sunan Muria dan bisa mengikuti petunjuk arah tersebut menuju gunung Muria dimana komplek pemakaman Sunan Muria berada.
textTranslated:
Sunan Muria's grave is located on the slopes of Mount Muria in Kudus Regency, Central Java, or to be precise, the address is Colo Village, Dawe District, Kab. Holy. Around his grave, there are 17 graves of soldiers and courtiers who were believed to be his bodyguards.

Sunan Muria's tomb is not like the tombs of other saints, this tomb is located at an altitude of 1600 meters above sea level, precisely on the slopes of Muria, which is located in Colo Village, Kudus, Central Java. To get to Sunan Muria's grave, just travel to Kudus. Before the Kudus Tower mosque there are directions to the Sunan Muria Tomb and you can follow these directions to Mount Muria where the Sunan Muria burial complex is located.
title: Tomb of Sunan Muria

text:
Alhamdulillah, saya diberi kesempatan untuk menziarahi Makam Sunan Muria sebelum Ramadhan. Seperti biasa, peziarah lain juga berdatangan. Kondisi di sana lumayan ramai. Bahkan, untuk masuk ke dalam makam, kami sampai berdesakan. Untuk itu, harap hati-hati dengan barang berharga Anda.

Siapa sangka, tangga menuju makam ada banyak. Mungkin benar-benar mencapai 1000 (🤭). Bagi yang tidak mau capek-capek menapaki tangga sebanyak itu, bisa memakai jasa ojek motor yang tersedia.

Di dalam makam, ada air yang bisa dibawa pulang. Katanya, itu dari sumber air yang digunakan untuk berwudhu Sunan Muria. Kalau mau membawanya pulang, tak perlu susah-susah membawa wadah air sendiri dari rumah. Di sana banyak yang berjualan, mulai dari botol plastik 1,5 liter sampai derigen kecil.

Saya sarankan jika datang dengan rombongan, harap jangan terpisah-pisah saat mengantri. Karena, yang diperbolehkan masuk pun dibatasi oleh petugas. Jika sampai terpisah, maka sisanya harus menunggu giliran lagi di luar.

Untuk urusan berbelanja, mungkin lebih baik dilakukan saat menuruni tangga saja (sepulang dari makam). Karena, ya ... Menaiki tangga sebanyak itu perlu tenaga ekstra untuk bisa sampai tanpa merasa ngos-ngosan. Saat belanja, saya punya satu rekomendasi, yaitu coklat. Kalau tidak salah, satu bungkus harganya 10k, isi 10. Bentuknya bukan coklat batangan. Tapi, seperti bubuk coklat yang dicetak. Mungkin tidak lebih baik dari Silverqueen, tapi enak kok.
textTranslated:
Thank God, I was given the opportunity to visit Sunan Muria's grave before Ramadhan. As usual, other pilgrims also arrived. Conditions there are quite busy. In fact, to get into the tomb, we were crowded together. For this reason, please be careful with your valuables.

Who would have thought, there are so many stairs to the tomb? It might actually reach 1000 (🤭). For those who don't want to get tired of climbing that many stairs, you can use the motorbike taxi services available.

Inside the tomb, there is water that you can take home. He said it was from the water source used for Sunan Muria's ablution. If you want to take it home, you don't need to bother bringing your own water container from home. There are lots of people selling there, ranging from 1.5 liter plastic bottles to small bottles.

I suggest that if you come with a group, please don't get separated when queuing. Because, what is allowed to enter is limited by the officers. If they are separated, the rest must wait their turn outside.

For shopping, it might be better to just go down the stairs (after returning from the grave). Because, yes... Climbing that many stairs requires extra energy to get there without feeling breathless. When shopping, I have one recommendation, namely chocolate. If I'm not mistaken, one pack costs 10k, contains 10. The shape is not a chocolate bar. But, like molded chocolate powder. Maybe not better than Silverqueen, but delicious nonetheless.
title: Tomb of Sunan Muria

name: mbah mbuh
text:
Sepatutnya kita menghormati leluhur.
Tp sangat disayangkan apabila kita mau ziarah pas kebetulan tdk tau jadwal buka tutup berkunjung.

Mhn maaf ini pengalaman kami sewaktu berkunjung di makam PB Imogiri Bantul dan kami tulis dg sebenarnya.

Sewaktu kami berkunjung pd Rabu 21/10/2020 (tutup) bisa ziarah asal membayar utk buka portal 50.000,- (kami bayar, kami pikir nanti di atas tinggal naik dan ziarah).
Sampai di area makam, masuk gerbang PB dan diajak ngobrol oleh abdi dalem.
Dikatakan bahwa saat ini sdg tutup, bisa masuk ziarah dg biaya yg fantastis
1. Ijin 2 (dua) juru kunci Jogja Solo @200.000,-
2. Pengiring ada 13 orang @50.000,-
3  Sewa pakaian per orang 15.000,-
4. Donasi se-ikhlasnya.

Fantastis ya...

Kami urung utk ziarah, jd pengeluaran kami hanya 50.000,- plus parkir yg di getok uang parkir kurang dr ½ jam 20.000,-
Utk pengunjung yg menggunakan mobil, siapkan uang parkir ya, apalagi yg nginap bisa sampai 150.000,- (area parkir di halaman depan gerbang gapura PB).
textTranslated:
We should respect our ancestors.
But it would be a shame if we wanted to make a pilgrimage when we happened to not know the opening and closing schedule for visiting.

Sorry, this is our experience when visiting the PB Imogiri Bantul grave and we are writing it truthfully.

When we visited on Wednesday 21/10/2020 (closed) you could go on a pilgrimage as long as you paid 50,000 to open the portal (we paid, we thought after that we would just go up and make the pilgrimage).
Arriving at the tomb area, enter the PB gate and be invited to chat by the courtiers.
It is said that currently it is closed, you can enter the pilgrimage at a fantastic cost
1. Permit for 2 (two) Jogja Solo caretakers @ 200,000,-
2. There are 13 accompanying people @ 50,000,-
3 Rent clothes per person 15,000,-
4. Donate sincerely.

Fantastic huh...

We refused to go on a pilgrimage, so our expenses were only 50,000,- plus parking which was charged for less than ½ hour, 20,000,-
For visitors who use cars, prepare parking money, especially for those staying overnight it can be up to 150,000,- (parking area in the front yard of the PB gate).

name: Mileadhamar
text:
Wilayah ini adalah kompleks pemakaman, masjid, dan di sekitarnya terdapat pasar. Merupakan objek wisata religi, sejarah, dan budaya.

Bangunan dan gapura yg ada sangat khas nuansa Mataram pada jaman dahulu. Suasana sejuk sekaligus sakral menyelimuti tempat ini.

Di dalamnya terdapat masjid agung kotagedhe yg masih berfungsi dan sangat terawat hingga sekarang. Selain itu juga terdapat pemandian yg dibagi menjadi 2, yaitu putri / putra yg di dalamnya terdapat sumber mata air yg biasanya digunakan untuk mandi / sekedar membasuh muka.

Khusus untuk wilayah makam, diwajibkan untuk memakai baju adat dan kemben (wanita) yg bisa disewa dgn tarif ± Rp 35.000,-

Lokasi parkir cukup luas, di sekitarnya terdapat warung makan, dan toko" aksesoris sebagai cinderamata.
textTranslated:
This area is a cemetery complex, mosque, and around it there is a market. It is a religious, historical and cultural tourist attraction.

The existing buildings and gates are very typical of the feel of Mataram in ancient times. A cool and sacred atmosphere surrounds this place.

Inside there is the Kotagedhe grand mosque which is still functioning and very well maintained to this day. Apart from that, there are also baths which are divided into 2, namely women's / men's, in which there is a spring which is usually used for bathing or just washing your face.

Especially for the grave area, you are required to wear traditional clothes and a kemben (women) which can be rented at a rate of ± IDR 35,000,-

The parking area is quite large, around it there are food stalls and accessories shops as souvenirs.
title: Makam Raja-Raja Mataram Kotagede

address: 59CX+3HP, Jl. Masjid Besar Mataram, Sayangan, Jagalan, Banguntapan, Bantul Regency, Special Region of Yogyakarta 55192, Indonesia
name: Hartono Budi
text:
Makam Raja-raja Kotagede adalah peninggalan kerajaan Mataram Islam pada abad 17, dibawah Rajanya yang pertama Danang Sutawijaya bergelar Panembahan Senopati.

Tiket free hanya bayar Parkir 3.000, untuk masuk ke dalam makam, wajib mengenakan busana Jawa. Busana bisa disewa di sekretariat 35.000. Pengunjung tidak diperbolehkan untuk memotret dan mengenakan perhiasan emas di dalam bangunan makam.

Selain Panembahan Senopati disini juga dimakamkan ayah Panembahan Senopati, yakni Ki Ageng Pemanahan, Sultan Hadiwijaya Raja Pajang, dan Sri Sultan Hamengkubuwono II.

Di Yogyakarta ada dua kompleks makam raja-raja Mataram Islam, yakni di Imogiri dan Kotagede. Dari kedua makam tersebut, makam raja-raja di Kotage yang usianya lebih tua. Letak Makam Kotagede berada di lokasi awal Kerajaan Mataram Islam berdiri.
textTranslated:
The Tombs of the Kotagede Kings are a relic of the Islamic Mataram kingdom in the 17th century, under its first King Danang Sutawijaya who had the title Panembahan Senopati.

Free tickets only pay 3,000 for parking. To enter the tomb, you must wear Javanese clothing. Clothing can be rented at the secretariat for 35,000. Visitors are not allowed to take photos or wear gold jewelry inside the tomb building.

Apart from Panembahan Senopati, Panembahan Senopati's father is also buried here, namely Ki Ageng Pemanahan, Sultan Hadiwijaya Raja Pajang, and Sri Sultan Hamengkubuwono II.

In Yogyakarta there are two tomb complexes of the Islamic Mataram kings, namely in Imogiri and Kotagede. Of the two tombs, the tombs of the kings in Kotage are older. The location of the Kotagede Tomb is at the initial location where the Islamic Mataram Kingdom was founded.
title: Makam Raja-Raja Mataram Kotagede

name: sunsuri
text:
Kadipaten Pakualaman (Hanacaraka: ꧋ꦑꦢꦶꦥꦠꦺꦤ꧀ꦦꦏꦸꦄꦭꦩ꧀ꦩꦤ꧀꧈ ) atau Nagari Pakualaman adalah negara dependen yang berbentuk kerajaan. Kedaulatan dan kekuasaan pemerintahan negara diatur dan dilaksanakan menurut perjanjian/kontrak politik yang dibuat oleh negara induk bersama-sama negara dependen. Sebagai konsekuensi dari bentuk negara kesatuan yang dipilih oleh Republik Indonesia sebagai negara induk, maka pada tahun 1950 status negara dependen Kadipaten Pakualaman (bersama-sama dengan Kesultanan Ngayogyakarta Hadiningrat) diturunkan menjadi daerah istimewa setingkat provinsi dengan nama Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta.
Semula Puro Paku Alaman merupakan Lembaga Istana yang mengurusi raja dan keluarga kerajaan disamping menjadi pusat pemerintahan Kadipaten Paku Alaman. Setelah Kadipaten Paku Alaman bersama-sama Kesultanan Yogyakarta diubah statusnya dari negara menjadi Daerah Istimewa setingkat Provinsi secara resmi pada 1950, Puro Paku Alaman mulai dipisahkan dari Pemerintahan Daerah Istimewa dan di-depolitisasi sehingga hanya menjadi sebuah Lembaga Pemangku Adat Jawa khususnya garis/gaya Paku Alaman Yogyakarta. Fungsi Puro Paku Alaman berubah menjadi pelindung dan penjaga identitas budaya Jawa khususnya gaya Paku Alaman Yogyakarta. Budaya Jawa gaya Paku Alaman ini kurang begitu terlihat dan berpengaruh di Yogyakarta mengingat wilayah Kadipaten Paku Alam yang kecil dan terletak jauh di pantai selatan Kabupaten Kulon Progo sekarang.
Namun ada perbedaan antara Puro Paku Alaman Yogyakarta dengan Istana kerajaan-kerajaan Nusantara yang lain. Sri Paduka Paku Alam selain sebagai Yang Dipertuan Pemangku Tahta Adat /Kepala Puro Paku Alaman juga memiliki kedudukan yang khusus dalam bidang pemerintahan sebagai bentuk keistimewaan daerah Yogyakarta. Dari permulaan DIY berdiri (de facto 1946 dan de yure 1950) sampai tahun 1998 Sri Paduka Paku Alam secara otomatis diangkat sebagai Wakil Gubernur/Wakil Kepala Daerah Istimewa yang tidak terikat dengan ketentuan masa jabatan, syarat, dan cara pengangkatan Wakil Gubernur/Wakil Kepala Daerah lainnya (UU 22/1948; UU 1/1957; Pen Pres 6/1959; UU 18/1965; UU 5/1974). Antara 1988-1998 Wakil Gubernur/Wakil Kepala Daerah Istimewa ditunjuk sebagai penjabat jabatan Gubernur/Kepala Daerah Istimewa. Setelah 1999 keturunan Sri Paduka Paku Alam tersebut yang memenuhi syarat mendapat prioritas untuk diangkat menjadi Wakil Gubernur/Wakil Kepala Daerah Istimewa (UU 22/1999; UU 32/2004). Saat ini yang menjadi Yang Dipertuan Pemangku Tahta adalah Sri Paduka Paku Alam IX
textTranslated:
Duchy of Pakualaman (Hanacaraka: ꧋ꦑꦢꦶꦥꦠꦺꦤ꧀ꦦꦏꦸꦄꦭꦩ꧀ꦩꦤ꧀꧈ ) or Nagari Pakualaman is a dependent state in the form of a kingdom. The sovereignty and power of the state government are regulated and implemented according to political agreements/contracts made by the parent country together with dependent countries. As a consequence of the unitary state form chosen by the Republic of Indonesia as the parent country, in 1950 the status of the dependent state of the Kadipaten Pakualaman (together with the Ngayogyakarta Hadiningrat Sultanate) was reduced to a special region at the provincial level with the name Yogyakarta Special Region.
Originally, Puro Paku Alaman was a palace institution that looked after the king and royal family as well as being the center of government for the Duchy of Paku Alaman. After the Duchy of Paku Alaman together with the Sultanate of Yogyakarta changed their status from a state to a Special Region at the provincial level officially in 1950, Puro Paku Alaman began to be separated from the Special Region Government and depoliticized so that it only became a Javanese Customary Institution, especially in the Paku Alaman line/style. Yogyakarta. The function of Puro Paku Alaman has changed to become the protector and guardian of Javanese cultural identity, especially the Yogyakarta Paku Alaman style. This Paku Alaman style of Javanese culture is less visible and influential in Yogyakarta considering that the Duchy of Paku Alam is small and located far on the south coast of Kulon Progo Regency today.
However, there are differences between Puro Paku Alaman Yogyakarta and the palaces of other Indonesian kingdoms. Sri Paduka Paku Alam, apart from being the Dipertuan Holder of the Traditional Throne/Head of Puro Paku Alaman, also has a special position in the field of government as a form of regional privilege in Yogyakarta. From the beginning of DIY's founding (de facto 1946 and de yure 1950) until 1998 Sri Paduka Paku Alam was automatically appointed as Deputy Governor/Deputy Head of the Special Region who was not bound by the terms of office, conditions and method of appointment of the Deputy Governor/Deputy Regional Head others (Law 22/1948; Law 1/1957; Pen Pres 6/1959; Law 18/1965; Law 5/1974). Between 1988-1998 the Deputy Governor/Deputy Head of the Special Region was appointed as acting Governor/Head of the Special Region. After 1999, descendants of Sri Paduka Paku Alam who met the requirements received priority to be appointed as Deputy Governor/Deputy Head of the Special Region (UU 22/1999; UU 32/2004). Currently the Dipertuan Regent of the Throne is Sri Paduka Paku Alam IX

name: ankqoen poo
text:
Puro Paku Alaman (bahasa Jawa: Pura Pakualaman) adalah bekas Istana kecil Kadipaten Paku Alaman. Istana ini menjadi tempat tinggal resmi para Pangeran Paku Alam mulai tahun 1813 sampai dengan tahun 1950, ketika pemerintah Negara Bagian Republik Indonesia menjadikan Kadipaten Paku Alaman (bersama-sama Kesultanan Yogyakarta) sebagai sebuah daerah berotonomi khusus setingkat provinsi yang bernama Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta.
Arsitektur dan Tata ruang	Sunting

Puro Paku Alaman ini adalah sebuah istana kecil jika dibandingkan dengan Keraton Yogyakarta. Ini menunjukkan kedudukan kadipaten ini yang walaupun sebagai negara berdaulat sendiri di luar Kesultanan Yogyakarta namun tetap setingkat di bawahnya. Istana ini menghadap ke arah selatan (sekarang Jalan Sultan Agung). Di depannya juga terdapat sebuah tanah lapang kecil, Alun-alun Sewandanan. Masjid Besar Pakualaman terdapat di sebelah barat daya istana. Arsitektur masjid mirip dengan masjid raya kesultanan namun dalam skala lebih kecil dan sederhana. Di dalamnya juga terdapat mimbar dan maksura, tempat khusus untuk Pangeran Paku Alam, seperti yang juga terdapat di masjid raya kesultanan tersebut.

Istana ini diapit oleh jalan umum di sisi utara(Jl. Purwanggan), timur (Jl. Harjono), dan selatan (Jl. Sewandanan). Gerbang istana Paku Alaman terdapat di sisi selatan (gerbang utama) dan sisi utara (sudah ditutup, namun masih ada bekas-bekasnya). Konon dulu istana ini juga dikelilingi benteng baluwerti  yang tidak beranjungan. Konon tembok tebal sepanjang dua puluh meter di sisi utara Jalan Sultan Agung sebelah timur pertigaan dengan Jalan Jagalan dipercaya sebagai bekas baluwarti tersebut. Gerbangnya konon terdapat di ujung selatan Jalan Gajah Mada.

Puro Paku Alaman masih menjadi tempat kediaman resmi Sri Paduka Paku Alam IX, yang juga wakil gubernur Provinsi Daerah Istimewa Yogyakarta. Bagian yang dapat dilihat oleh umum adalah pendapa terdepan yang disebut dengan Bangsal Sewatama. Sementara itu, bagian yang terbuka untuk dimasuki umum hanyalah bagian Museum Puro Pakualaman.
textTranslated:
Puro Paku Alaman (Javanese: Pura Pakualaman) is the former small palace of the Duchy of Paku Alaman. This palace became the official residence of the Princes of Paku Alam from 1813 until 1950, when the government of the Republic of Indonesia made the Duchy of Paku Alaman (together with the Sultanate of Yogyakarta) a special autonomous region at the provincial level called the Special Region of Yogyakarta.
Architecture and Spatial Planning Edit

Puro Paku Alaman is a small palace compared to the Yogyakarta Palace. This shows the position of this duchy, which, even though it is a sovereign state outside the Sultanate of Yogyakarta, is still a level below it. This palace faces south (now Jalan Sultan Agung). In front of it there is also a small field, Alun-alun Sewandanan. The Pakualaman Great Mosque is located to the southwest of the palace. The architecture of the mosque is similar to the sultanate's grand mosque but on a smaller and simpler scale. Inside there is also a pulpit and maksura, a special place for Prince Paku Alam, as is also found in the sultanate's grand mosque.

This palace is flanked by public roads on the north (Jl. Purwanggan), east (Jl. Harjono), and south (Jl. Sewandanan). The Paku Alaman palace gate is on the south side (main gate) and the north side (it has been closed, but there are still traces of it). It is said that in the past this palace was also surrounded by the Baluwerti fort which did not have a platform. It is said that the twenty meter thick wall on the north side of Jalan Sultan Agung east of the T-junction with Jalan Jagalan is believed to be the former baluwarti. The gate is said to be at the southern end of Jalan Gajah Mada.

Puro Paku Alaman is still the official residence of Sri Paduka Paku Alam IX, who is also the deputy governor of the Special Region of Yogyakarta Province. The part that can be seen by the public is the front pavilion called Bangsal Sewatama. Meanwhile, the only part that is open to the public is the Puro Pakualaman Museum.

address: Pasarean, Pesarean, Adiwerna, Tegal Regency, Central Java 52194, Indonesia
name: Masribi _120
text:
Aset Nasional yang Bisa Jadi Wisata Religi di Kabupaten Tegal. Tak hanya sentra industri pengolahan dan pengecoran logam saja, Desa Pesarean, Kecamatan Adiwerna, Kabupaten Tegal dikenal memiliki situs peninggalan sejarah dan kepurbakalaan. Situs ini banyak dikenali, baik warga lokal maupun luar Kabupaten Tegal. Bahkan, wisatawan mancanegara pun juga tertarik mengunjungi peninggalan sejarah di DesaPesarean.
Situs kepurbakalaan ini berlokasi sekitar delapan kilometer dari ibukota Kabupaten Tegal, Kota Slawi. Berada di atas lahan seluas 13.000 meter persegi yang dikelilingi tembok tebal batu bata merah, peninggalan sejarah ini mirip bangunan zaman kerajaan. Bukan candi maupun benteng/istana kerajaan, tetapi peninggalan kepurbakalaan di Desa Pesarean ini adalah Makam Tegal Arum. Sebuah tempat peristirahatan Kanjeng Sultan Amangkurat Agung (Amangkurat I), raja Kesultanan Mataram yang berkuasa sejak tahun 1646-1677. Berdasarkan catatan sejarah, Amangkurat I merupakan putera ke-10 dari pasangan Raja Mataram Islam,Kanjeng Sultan Agung Prabu Hanyakrakusumo (berkuasa 1613- 1645) dengan permaisuri kedua Raden Ayu Wetan.Tahun 1646, Amangkurat I membangun Masjid Agung Ngeksi Ganda di pusat pemerintahan di Plered. Namun, pada tahun 1676, keraton Plered diserbu pemberontak Trunojoyo dan Kraeng Galesong dari Makasar. Karena itu, Amangkurat I lari ke arah Batavia. Di tengah perjalanan Ajibarang, Kabupaten Tegal, beliau meninggal dunia. Kemudian, disemayamkan di Tegal Arum, tepatnya tanggal 13 Juli 1677.Kini, Makam Tegal Arum yang terletak di depan Balai Desa Pesarean, Adiwerna masih terus dikenang. Banyak orang ziarah kemakam Amangkurat I yang jasadnya diyakini masih utuh itu. Makam raja ini memiliki bentuk rumah tajuk dengan konstruksi danbahan bangunan terbuat dari kayu jati. Tempat pemakaman itu juga dikelilingi batu bata merah.Kompleks Makam Tegal Arum ini juga menjadi tempat peristirahatan bagi para abdi dalem (pembantu) Amangkurat I beserta pengikut dan keturunannya. Makam itu mengelilingi tempat peristirahatan utama sang raja. Di makam ini pula, disemayamkan R.A. Kardinah (adik dari RA Kartini) yang merupakan pendiri RSUD Kardinah
AMANGKURAT 1 memang memiliki AJI PANCASONYA, beliau membunuh orang2 muslim karena beliau tidak suka dengan PAHAM WAHABI yang berkembang diwilayah jawa, sedangkan arab saudi disaat yang sama sebagai sumber paham wahabi, maka AMANGKURAT murka karena beliau
tidak senang rakyatnya berpindah aliran dari KEJAWEN ke wahabi. setelah orang² wahabi dihabisi beliau lari ke batavia akan tetapi baru sampai kota TEGAL beliau wafat dan dimakamkan di tegal oleh masyarakat tegal beliau disebut SUNAN AMANGKURAT TEGAL ARUM.

Tepatnya di desa pesarean RT 20/05 kecamatan Adiwerna.
disamping itu juga ada makam sesepuh desa pesarean, almagfurllah KH. Sholeh, dan Kyai Syamsudin (Mbah lembahmanah)
textTranslated:
National Assets that Can Become Religious Tourism in Tegal Regency. Not only is it a center for the metal processing and casting industry, Pesarean Village, Adiwerna District, Tegal Regency is known to have historical and archeological heritage sites. This site is widely known, both local residents and outside Tegal Regency. In fact, foreign tourists are also interested in visiting historical heritage in Pesarean Village.
This archaeological site is located about eight kilometers from the capital of Tegal Regency, Slawi City. Situated on an area of ​​13,000 square meters surrounded by thick walls of red brick, this historical heritage resembles a building from the royal era. Not a temple or a fort/royal palace, but an ancient relic in Pesarean Village is the Tegal Arum Tomb. A resting place for Kanjeng Sultan Amangkurat Agung (Amangkurat I), the king of the Mataram Sultanate who ruled from 1646-1677. Based on historical records, Amangkurat I was the 10th son of the couple of the Islamic Mataram King, Kanjeng Sultan Agung Prabu Hanyakrakusumo (r. 1613-1645) with his second queen, Raden Ayu Wetan. In 1646, Amangkurat I built the Ngeksi Ganda Grand Mosque in the government center in Plered. . However, in 1676, the Plered palace was attacked by Trunojoyo and Kraeng Galesong rebels from Makasar. Because of this, Amangkurat I ran towards Batavia. In the middle of his journey to Ajibarang, Tegal Regency, he died. Then, he was buried in Tegal Arum, precisely on July 13, 1677. Today, the Tegal Arum Tomb which is located in front of the Pesarean Village Hall, Adiwerna is still remembered. Many people visit the grave of Amangkurat I, whose body is believed to be still intact. This king's tomb has the shape of a canopy house with construction and building materials made of teak wood. The burial place is also surrounded by red bricks. The Tegal Arum Tomb Complex is also a resting place for the servants of Amangkurat I and their followers and descendants. The tombs surround the king's main resting place. In this tomb, R.A. Kardinah (sister of RA Kartini) who is the founder of RSUD Kardinah
AMANGKURAT 1 indeed had AJI PANCASONYA, he killed Muslims because he didn't like the WAHABI ideology which was developing in the Java region, while Saudi Arabia at the same time was the source of Wahhabi ideology, so AMANGKURAT was angry because of him.
not happy with the people switching from KEJAWEN to Wahhabi. After the Wahhabi people were killed, he fled to Batavia, but before he reached the city of TEGAL, he died and was buried in Tegal by the people of Tegal. He was called SUNAN AMANGKURAT TEGAL ARUM.

To be precise, in Pesarean village, RT 20/05, Adiwerna sub-district.
Besides that, there is also the grave of the Pesarean village elder, Almagfurllah KH. Sholeh, and Kyai Syamsudin (Mbah Lembahmanah)

text: Sunan Muria merupakan salah satu dari 9 (sembilan) wali atau wali songo yang terkenal di kalangan wisata religi di pulau Jawa. Lokasinya di gunung Muria. Untuk bisa ke makam, bisa dengan jalan kaki menaiki tangga yang cukup melelahkan atau naik ojek yang sudah disediakan pengelola. Di lokasi masjid makam sunan Muria terdapat berbagai macam jualan oleh-oleh khas Kudus. Hawanya sejuk dan dingin jadi bisa membawa jaket. Untuk lokasi parkir cukup luas bisa menampung bis besar.
textTranslated: Sunan Muria is one of the 9 (nine) wali or songo saints who are famous among religious tourism on the island of Java. The location is on Mount Muria. To get to the tomb, you can walk up the stairs which is quite tiring or take a motorbike taxi that has been provided by the management. At the location of the Sunan Muria tomb mosque, there are various kinds of typical Kudus souvenirs for sale. The air is cool and cold so you can bring a jacket. The parking location is large enough to accommodate large buses.
title: Tomb of Sunan Muria

text: Makam Sunan Muria merupakan salah satu bukti arkeologis yang berkenaan dengan masa awal perkembangan Islam di Jawa khusunya di wilayah Kudus, Pati dan sekitarnya. Kompleks Makam Sunan Muria berada di Bukit Muria yang terletak di Desa Colo, Kecamatan Dawe, Kabupaten Kudus, Provinsi Jawa Tengah dan berada pada ketinggian lebih dari 1600 meter di atas permukaan laut.
textTranslated: Sunan Muria's tomb is one of the archaeological evidence relating to the early development of Islam in Java, especially in the Kudus, Pati and surrounding areas. The Sunan Muria Tomb Complex is on Muria Hill which is located in Colo Village, Dawe District, Kudus Regency, Central Java Province and is at an altitude of more than 1600 meters above sea level.

address: Pasarean, Pesarean, Adiwerna, Tegal Regency, Central Java 52194, Indonesia
name: Ma'rufin Sudibyo
text:
Makam Sri Susuhunan Amangkurat Agung (Amangkurat I), raja Mataram yang "tak terkira kekejamannya." Bertahta 1646 - 1677 dg berpusat di Keraton Plered.

Salah satu aksi kekejamannya yg melegenda adalah peristiwa Pembantaian ± 6.000 orang (ulama se-Mataram beserta keluarganya) pada 1648 di alun-alun Plered. Atas tuduhan terlibat kudeta. Seluruh ulama itu sesungguhnya masih keluarga Amangkurat I, tepatnya keluarga besar Kajoran (keluarga salah satu permaisurinya).

Kekejaman Amangkurat I akhirnya berujung pemberontakan Trunajaya. Keraton Plered diduduki Trunajaya & Amangkurat I memilih melarikan diri ke barat, hendak mencari perlindungan VOC di Batavia/Jakarta. Namun di Tegalwangi ia jatuh sakit dan wafat.
textTranslated:
The tomb of Sri Susuhunan Amangkurat Agung (Amangkurat I), the king of Mataram whose "uncountable cruelty." Reigned 1646 - 1677 based in Plered Palace.

One of his legendary acts of cruelty was the Massacre of ± 6,000 people (Mataram scholars and their families) in 1648 in Plered square. On charges of being involved in a coup. All the scholars are actually still the family of Amangkurat I, to be precise the extended family of Kajoran (the family of one of his queens).

The cruelty of Amangkurat I finally led to the rebellion of Trunajaya. Plered Palace was occupied by Trunajaya & Amangkurat I chose to flee to the west, wanting to seek VOC protection in Batavia/Jakarta. But in Tegalwangi he fell ill and died.
title: Situs Makam Sunan Amangkurat Agung

Makam Imogiri berada di atas bukit Imogiri  yang lumayan tinggi merupakan makam Raja raja Mataram dan Yogyakarta.Untuk naik ke atas kita harus melewati beberapa anak tangga yang jumlahnya lebih dari 400 an.Tapi anehnya setiap orang hitungannya selalu berbeda.Saya pernah memcobanya mungkin karena ngos ngosan kecapaian malah lupa hitungannya.

Untuk bisa masuk sampai  pemakanan tidak semua orang boleh masuk harus ijin juri kunci dan memakai pakain jawa.Belum lama kesana parkir dan naik keatas cuma masukin kotak saja.Kalau ke Imogiri jangan lupa kuliner terkenal Wedang uwuh dan pecelnya-tahu bacem-tempe bacem, banyak yang jualan di sekitar parkiran mobil.Selain Makam raja Imogiri tidak jauh ada makam seniman juga museum Giri Sapto.Jarak Imogiri dari kota Jogja sekitar 18 km bisa di lalui pakai semua kendaraan dari bis-mobil-motor-sepeda atau online karena jalannya mulus lebar dan datar.
textTranslated:
The Imogiri Tomb is on the top of the Imogiri Hill which is quite high, which is the tomb of the kings of Mataram and Yogyakarta. To climb to the top we have to go through several stairs, which number more than 400. But strangely, everyone's count is always different. I tried it, maybe because I was out of breath. I was so tired that I forgot to count.

To be able to enter until the burial, not everyone can enter, you have to get permission from the key judge and wear Javanese clothes. It's not long before you get there, park and go upstairs, just put it in the box. If you go to Imogiri, don't forget the famous culinary delights Wedang Uwuh and pecel - tofu bacem and tempeh bacem, lots of them. which sells around the car park. Apart from the Imogiri king's grave, not far away there is an artist's grave as well as the Giri Sapto museum. The distance between Imogiri from the city of Jogja is around 18 km and can be accessed using all vehicles, from bus, car, motorbike, bicycle or online because the road is wide and smooth. flat.
title: Makam Raja-Raja Imogiri

name: reza prisma
text: Makam raja-raja mataram.Makam Imogiri merupakan kompleks makam Raja-Raja Mataram Islam beserta keturunannya, yakni Raja-raja yang bertahta di Kasunanan Surakarta Hadiningrat dan Kasultanan Ngayogyakarta Hadiningrat. Kompleks Makam Imogoro terletak di Kecamatan Imogiri, Kabupaten Bantul dan dibangun pada tahun 1632 oleh Sultan Agung Hanyokrokusumo. Konon, Sultan Agung sudah mempersiapkan makam tersebut sebelum dirinya wafat. Di kerajaan Mataram Islam, tersebutlah raja bernama Sultan Agung Hanyokrokusumo atau lebih dikenal dengan nama Sultan Agung. Ia merupakan raja ke-3 Krajaan Mataram islam yang terkenal arif dan bijaksana. Di bawah kepemimpinannya, rakyat Mataram senantiasa hidup aman, tenteram, dan makmur. Itulah sebabnya, ia sangat dicintai dan dihormati rakyatnya. Selain kharismatik, Sultan Agung memiliki kesaktian yang tinggi. Konon, ia mampu ke Mekah secara gaib untuk Sholat Jumat di sana. Karena seringnya ke Mekah, Sultan Agung kenal baik dengan beberapa ulama di sana, baik ulama Arab maupun ulama dari Indonesia yang sedang berada di Mekah.
textTranslated: Tombs of the kings of Mataram. Imogiri Tombs is a complex of tombs of the Islamic Kings of Mataram and their descendants, namely the Kings who reigned in the Surakarta Hadiningrat Sultanate and the Ngayogyakarta Hadiningrat Sultanate. The Imogoro Tomb Complex is located in Imogiri District, Bantul Regency and was built in 1632 by Sultan Agung Hanyokrokusumo. It is said that Sultan Agung had prepared the tomb before he died. In the Islamic kingdom of Mataram, the king is called Sultan Agung Hanyokrokusumo or better known as Sultan Agung. He is the 3rd king of Islamic Mataram Kingdom who is famously wise and wise. Under his leadership, the people of Mataram always lived in peace, tranquility, and prosperity. That is why, it is loved and respected by its people. In addition to being charismatic, Sultan Agung has a high level of magic. It is said that he was able to go to Mecca magically for Friday Prayers there. Because of his frequent visits to Mecca, Sultan Agung was well acquainted with several scholars there, both Arab scholars and scholars from Indonesia who were currently in Mecca.
title: Makam Raja-Raja Imogiri

name: AW Wibowo
text:
Lokasi tepat berada di selatan pasar kota gede. Dekat dengan keramaian

Akses masuk lokasi lumayan mudah meski jln nya agak sempit dan ramai.

Parkir luas bsa muat puluhan mobil dan motor.

Masuk lokasi masjid dan sendang tidak ada biaya retribusi, Kecuali masuk area makam. Dn diwajibkan pakai pakaian adat jawa.

Fasilitas cukup lengkap. Dengan suasana masjid dan halaman sejuk asri.

Kotagede merupakan salah satu kawasan bersejarah yang ada di Yogyakarta. Selain terkenal sebagai penghasil perak unggulan, Kotagede juga menyimpan berbagai bangunan bersejarah. Salah satu bangunan bersejarah yang ada di Kotagede adalah Masjid Mataram Kotagede.

Masjid Mataram Kotagede didirikan tahun 1640 atas prakarsa Sultan Agung dan dibantu oleh warga sekitar Kotagede yang saat itu banyak menganut agama Hindu dan Budha. Pengaruh Hindu dan Budha juga dapat terlihat dari berbagai ornamen yang ada di masjid berusia ratusan tahun ini.

Di sekitar masjid, terdapat sebuah prasasti yang menceritakan proses pembangunan masjid ini. Menurut keterangan pada prasasti, masjid ini dibangun dalam dua tahap. Tahap pertama dilakukan oleh Sultan Agung. Bangunan masjid saat itu masih kecil, atau biasa disebut langgar. Pada tahap kedua, pembangunan masjid diteruskan oleh Pakubuwono X, selaku Raja Kesultanan Surakarta.
textTranslated:
The location is right south of the big city market. Close to the crowds

Access to the location is quite easy even though the road is a bit narrow and busy.

Ample parking can accommodate dozens of cars and motorbikes.

There is no retribution fee to enter the mosque location and there is no fee, except for entering the grave area. And you are required to wear traditional Javanese clothing.

The facilities are quite complete. With a mosque atmosphere and a cool, beautiful courtyard.

Kotagede is one of the historical areas in Yogyakarta. Apart from being famous as a superior silver producer, Kotagede also has various historical buildings. One of the historical buildings in Kotagede is the Mataram Kotagede Mosque.

The Mataram Kotagede Mosque was founded in 1640 on the initiative of Sultan Agung and assisted by residents around Kotagede who at that time mostly adhered to Hindu and Buddhist religions. Hindu and Buddhist influences can also be seen from the various ornaments in this centuries-old mosque.

Around the mosque, there is an inscription that tells the story of the construction process of this mosque. According to the information on the inscription, this mosque was built in two stages. The first stage was carried out by Sultan Agung. The mosque building at that time was still small, or what was usually called a langgar. In the second stage, the construction of the mosque was continued by Pakubuwono X, as King of the Surakarta Sultanate.

name: ana fatkul
text:
Peraturan jika masuk makam :
1. Jam operasional untuk umum berziarah adalah Senin, Kamis, Jumat dan Minggu
2. Wajib melepas alas kaki saat masuk ke dalam makam.
3. Di dalam makam sama sekali tidak boleh mengambil gambar alias memotret.
4. Ketika masuk ke dalam makam, wanita wajib mengenakan kemben dan kain jarik serta melepas jilbab.
5. Laki-laki diwajibkan mengenakan pakaian abdi dalem yakni blangkon dan juga kain jarik.
6. Perlengkapan atau pakaian dapat disewa di kantor sekretariat.
7. Selama Bulan Ramadhan Makam Raja-raja Mataram di Kotagede ini ditutup untuk umum.
Jika Anda memiliki pakaian tradisional atau abdi dalem bergaya Yogyakarta dan Surakarta, bisa Anda gunakan saat berziarah ke Makam Raja-raja Mataram di Kotagede ini.
Untuk sewa baju per orang Rp. 40.000, karena makam hari sabtu bukan jam oprasianal bisa masuk dengan ijin bayar Rp. 100.000.
textTranslated:
Rules for entering the tomb:
1. Operational hours for public pilgrimages are Monday, Thursday, Friday and Sunday
2. You must remove your footwear when entering the tomb.
3. In the tomb you are absolutely not allowed to take pictures or take photos.
4. When entering the tomb, women are required to wear a kemben and a jarik cloth and remove the hijab.
5. Men are required to wear courtiers' clothing, namely blangkon and also jarik cloth.
6. Equipment or clothing can be rented at the secretariat office.
7. During the month of Ramadan, the Tombs of the Mataram Kings in Kotagede are closed to the public.
If you have traditional clothes or courtiers in the Yogyakarta and Surakarta style, you can wear them when making a pilgrimage to the Tombs of the Mataram Kings in Kotagede.
To rent clothes per person Rp. 40,000, because the grave is not operational hours on Saturday, you can enter with permission to pay Rp. 100,000.
title: Makam Raja-Raja Mataram Kotagede

text: Lokasi cukup mudah dijangkau. Dekat pasar legi kotagede. Satu komplek dengan masjid gedhe mataram dan sendang selirang. Salah satu lokasi bersejarah dan sakral. Bila hendak masuk ke makam sama seperti di imogiri,harus menggunakan pakaian peranakan untuk pria dan untuk wanita memakai jarik dan kemben. Dilarang memakai perhiasan emas. Yang unik ada sebuah makam yang separo di dalam komplek pemakaman yang separo diluar. Itu adalah makam Ki Ageng Mangir yg merupakan musuh sekaligus menantu panembahan senopati. Tidak dipungut tiket. Hanya wajib melapor kepada juru kunci. Tidak diperkenankan motret dibeberapa spot.
textTranslated: The location is quite easy to reach. Near the Kotagede legi market. One complex with the big mosque in Mataram and Sendang Selirang. One of the historical and sacred locations. If you want to enter the tomb, just like in Imogiri, you have to wear Peranakan clothing for men and for women wear a jarik and kemben. It is forbidden to wear gold jewelry. What is unique is that there is a tomb that is half inside the cemetery complex and half outside. That is the grave of Ki Ageng Mangir who was the enemy and son-in-law of Panembahan Senopati. No tickets required. Only required to report to the caretaker. Photography is not permitted in some spots.
title: Makam Raja-Raja Mataram Kotagede

text:
Salah satu tempat yang memiliki nilai historis dan tujuan wisata juga menjadi tempat tinggal Sri Paku Alam yang bertahta di keraton Puro Paku Alaman saat ini...
Tempat yang masih terjaga keasliannya dan di dalamnya terdapat pula perpustakaan buku-buku kuno tentang perjalanan keraton Paku Alaman dari sejak jaman penjajahan kolonial dahulu, serta dapat dijumpai pula museum kereta kencana yang seringkali digunakan pada saat upacara-upacara adat di Puro Paku Alaman ini...
Memang tidak semua bagian dari Puro Paku Alaman ini dapat dikunjungi wisatawan karena memang ada sudut-sudut tertentu bangunan ini yang masih dijaga kesakralannya, sehingga tidak semua orang kecuali kerabat atau pun keluarga yang dapat memasukinya...
textTranslated:
One of the places that has historical value and is a tourist destination is also the residence of Sri Paku Alam, who currently reigns in the Puro Paku Alaman palace...
A place that still maintains its authenticity and in it there is also a library of ancient books about the travels of the Paku Alaman palace from the colonial colonial era, and you can also find a golden carriage museum which is often used during traditional ceremonies at Puro Paku Alaman. .
Indeed, not all parts of Puro Paku Alaman can be visited by tourists because there are certain corners of this building that are still kept sacred, so not everyone except relatives or family can enter it...
title: Pura Pakualaman

text: Museum ini dikelola oleh dinas kebudayaan DIY dan pura pakualaman. Berisi benda-benda peninggalan Paku Alam dan foto para Paku Alam yang pernah menjabat. Selain itu ada serat sepanjang 13meter yang mengisahkan mengenai manusia sejak jaman nabi Adam. Bagi yang ingin mengenal wilayah Pakualaman pada masa lampau (Adikarta di Kulon Progo) bisa berkunjung kesini karena ada peta yang dipajang mengenai wilayah Pakualaman pada masa tersebut.  Guide cukup informatif dan masuk ke museum tidak dipungut biaya hanya saja disarankan untuk memberikan donasi seiklasnya. Museum terletak di kompleks Keraton Pakualaman
textTranslated: This museum is managed by the DIY cultural service and the Pakualaman Temple. Contains Paku Alam heritage objects and photos of Paku Alam who have served. Apart from that, there is a 13 meter long fiber that tells the story of humans since the time of the prophet Adam. For those who want to get to know the Pakualaman area in the past (Adikarta in Kulon Progo) you can visit here because there is a map on display regarding the Pakualaman area at that time.  The guide is quite informative and entry to the museum is free, but it is recommended that you make a donation if you wish. The museum is located in the Pakualaman Palace complex

name: AURORA KIDS COLLECTIONS
text:
Sebelum dibangun kompleks makam raja-raja di Imogiri, Sultan Agung telah menyiapkan area pemakaman khusus yang dinamakan Girilaya. Perancangnya adalah paman sultan yang bernama Panembahan Juminah, salah satu putra Sutawijaya alias Panembahan Senapati, pendiri Kesultanan Mataram Islam.
Namun, di tengah proses pembangunan makam itu, Panembahan Juminah wafat. Sultan Agung membatalkan rencana penggunaan kompleks tersebut untuk raja-raja Mataram. Panembahan Juminah dikuburkan di Makam Girilaya sebagai bentuk penghormatan Sultan Agung kepada paman tercintanya tersebut.
textTranslated:
Before the kings' tomb complex was built in Imogiri, Sultan Agung had prepared a special burial area called Girilaya. The designer was the sultan's uncle, Panembahan Juminah, one of the sons of Sutawijaya alias Panembahan Senapati, founder of the Islamic Mataram Sultanate.
However, in the middle of the process of building the tomb, Panembahan Juminah died. Sultan Agung canceled plans to use the complex for the Mataram kings. Panembahan Juminah was buried in the Girilaya Cemetery as a form of Sultan Agung's respect for his beloved uncle.
title: Makam Raja-Raja Imogiri

name: sae sahbani
text: Makam Imogiri merupakan komplek makam bagi raja-raja mataram dan keluarganya yang berada di Ginirejo Imogiri kabupaten Bantul. Makam ini didirikan antara tahun 1632 - 1640M oleh Sultan Agung Adi Prabu Hanyokrokusumo, Sultan Mataram ke-3, keturunan dari  Panembahan Senopati, Raja Mataram ke-1, dan merupakan bangunan milik keraton kasultanan.
textTranslated: Imogiri Tomb is a tomb complex for Mataram kings and their families located in Ginirejo Imogiri, Bantul district. This tomb was founded between 1632 - 1640 AD by Sultan Agung Adi Prabu Hanyokrokusumo, the 3rd Sultan of Mataram, a descendant of Panembahan Senopati, the 1st King of Mataram, and is a building belonging to the Sultanate's palace.
title: Makam Raja-Raja Imogiri

text: Alhamdulillah diberi kesempatan Allah untuk ziarah ke makam sunan muria untuk ke tiga kalinya. Akses ke makam memang butuh effort, tidak seperti makam sunan kudus dan kalijaga. Kalau jalan kaki ya gitu, nanjak tapi ada anak tangga. Tp kalau mau lebih cepat dan gak capek, jasa ojek hanya Rp.15.000 (oktober 2021). Namun menurut saya justru lebih nyaman naik ojek, bonus dapat menikmati udara segar (track nya tentu menegangkan karena naik motor nanjak pula).
textTranslated: Thank God, Allah gave me the opportunity to visit Sunan Muria's grave for the third time. Access to the tomb does require effort, unlike the tombs of Sunan Kudus and Kalijaga. If you walk, it's like that, uphill but there are steps. But if you want it to be faster and not tired, motorbike taxi services are only IDR 15,000 (October 2021). However, in my opinion, it's actually more comfortable to ride a motorbike taxi, the bonus is that you can enjoy the fresh air (the track is certainly stressful because riding a motorbike is uphill too).
title: Tomb of Sunan Muria

name: Prasetyo Budi Widagdo
text:
Kompleks makam pendiri kerajaan Mataram berada sekitar 100 meter dari pasar Kotagede, dikelilingi tembok besar dan kokoh. Pintu Gapura memasuki kompleks makam ini masih memiliki ciri arsitektur budaya Hindu bernama Gapura paduraksa dengan kusen berukir di sebelah selatan Masjid Besar Mataram yang menuju ke dalam kompleks Makam Raja-Raja Mataram. Pada puncak gapura ini terdapat ukiran kepala Kala bercuping ganda terbuat dari batu kapur, namun ekspresi raut muka Kala ini tidak begitu garang.

Setiap gapura memiliki pintu kayu yang tebal dengan ukiran yang indah dan dijaga oleh sejumlah abdi dalem berbusana adat Jawa. Ada 3 gapura yang harus dilewati sebelum masuk ke bangunan makam. Uniknya, kita diharapkan untuk menggunakan busana adat jawa untuk memasuki area makam. Pengalaman menarik menggunakan busana layaknya abdi dalem kerajaan Jawa kuno. Kita akan melewati 3 gapura sebelum sampai ke gapura terakhir yang menuju bangunan makam.
textTranslated:
The tomb complex of the founder of the Mataram kingdom is located about 100 meters from the Kotagede market, surrounded by a large and sturdy wall. The Gapura door entering this tomb complex still has Hindu cultural architectural characteristics called Gapura paduraksa with carved frames to the south of the Mataram Great Mosque which leads into the Mataram Kings Tomb complex. At the top of this gate there is a carved head of Kala with double lobes made of limestone, but the expression on Kala's face is not so fierce.

Each gate has a thick wooden door with beautiful carvings and is guarded by a number of courtiers dressed in traditional Javanese clothing. There are 3 gates that must be passed before entering the tomb building. Uniquely, we are expected to wear traditional Javanese clothing to enter the tomb area. An interesting experience wearing clothes like courtiers from an ancient Javanese kingdom. We will pass through 3 gates before reaching the final gate which leads to the tomb building.
title: Makam Raja-Raja Mataram Kotagede

name: Zunan Arief
text:
Letak Makam Kotagede berada di samping Masjid Gedhe Mataram, Lokasi makam dan masjid tidak berubah sejak zaman dahulu hingga sekarang. Hingga saat ini Masjid Gedhe Mataram masih berfungsi sebagaimana masjid lainnya. Setiap waktu salat, terlebih salat Jumat, masjid ini selalu dipadati oleh jamaah. Sementara makam raja di Kotagede juga menjadi destinasi wisata religi selain Masjid Gedhe Mataram hingga kini. Kompleks makam tidak sebesar Imogiri, tetapi banyak orang yang berziarah di sini.
Makam Kotagede adalah tempat dikebumikannya raja pertama Mataram Islam, Danang Sutawijaya atau Panembahan Senopati. Raja kedua, yakni Mas Jolang atau Panembahan Hanyakrawati.
textTranslated:
The location of the Kotagede Tomb is next to the Gedhe Mataram Mosque. The location of the tomb and mosque has not changed since ancient times until now. Until now, the Gedhe Mataram Mosque still functions like other mosques. Every prayer time, especially Friday prayers, this mosque is always packed with worshipers. Meanwhile, the king's tomb in Kotagede is also a religious tourism destination apart from the Gedhe Mataram Mosque to this day. The tomb complex is not as big as Imogiri, but many people make pilgrimages here.
Kotagede Tomb is the burial place of the first king of Islamic Mataram, Danang Sutawijaya or Panembahan Senopati. The second king, namely Mas Jolang or Panembahan Hanyakrawati.
title: Makam Raja-Raja Mataram Kotagede

Tempat ini merupakan tempat yang sangat terhormat bagi orang Jawa sehingga pengunjung yang berwisata hendaknya tetap menjunjung tinggi norma kesopanan dan etika yang berlaku. textTranslated: In this place rest in peace the founders of the Mataram Kingdom. Visitors are allowed to pilgrimage at this place in accordance with applicable regulations. This place is very comfortable and quiet to visit. This complex offers typical Javanese architecture before today's modern Java. The first impression of visiting this place is that it feels like returning to home and family, warm and gentle. This place is a very honorable place for Javanese people so visitors who travel should still uphold the prevailing norms of politeness and etiquette. A night visit will provide an atmosphere that will be memorable for you. Welcome. Don't forget to pray for Mataram's ancestors, let's offer prayers to the Almighty.

title: Makam Raja-Raja Mataram Kotagede

address: 59CX+3HP, Jl. Masjid Besar Mataram, Sayangan, Jagalan, Banguntapan, Bantul Regency, Special Region of Yogyakarta 55192, Indonesia
name: Bramanditya issudibya
text: Makam atau tempat peristirahatan terakhir raja - raja dan pendiri mataram islam seperti panembahan senopati. Sultan HB II dan Paku alam I -IV juga dimakamkan disini. Bangunannya direnovasi saat Paku buwana X bertahta. Uniknya di makam kota gedhe adalah makam ki ageng mangir yang berada  setengah didalam bangunan dan setengah diluar bangunan. Apabila mengunjungi makam harus menggunakan busana jawa dan harus jaga sopan santun.
textTranslated: The tomb or final resting place of the kings and founders of Islamic Mataram such as Panembahan Senopati. Sultans HB II and Paku Alam I -IV are also buried here. The building was renovated when Paku Buwana X was on the throne. What is unique about the Kota Gede cemetery is the tomb of Ki Ageng Mangir which is half inside the building and half outside the building. When visiting the grave you must wear Javanese clothing and must maintain good manners.
title: Makam Raja-Raja Mataram Kotagede

text:
Dulu pas kecil bapak mamak pernah kesini.
Masuk kedalam kemudian diajak melihat ikan lele putih . Ada kepala dan ekor. Badanya duri atau tulang saja.
Kemudian oleh abdi dalemnya di pamitkan mau ke Sumatra. Dan abdi dalemnya memberi makan ikanya. Ikanya kayak berbaris. Kemudian air nya jernih. Lalu diambilkan airnya oleh abdi dalam dan di bawa ke sumatra. Kemudian di ajak keliling melihat tempat tempatnya. Ada batu bekas seorang anak yang durhaka ke pada ayahnya. Karna sakti kepalanya di jedotkan ke batu dan batunya penyok.
Pingin kesini.
textTranslated:
When I was little, my father and mother used to come here.
Go inside and be invited to see white catfish. There is a head and a tail. The body only has spines or bones.
Then his servants said goodbye to Sumatra. And his courtiers fed the fish. The fish seem to line up. Then the water is clear. Then the servant took the water and took it to Sumatra. Then they were invited to go around to see the place. There is a stone left by a child who disobeyed his father. Because of magic, his head was sucked into a rock and the rock was dented.
Want to come here.
title: Makam Raja-Raja Mataram Kotagede

text:
Nama Sunan Muria sendiri diperkirakan berasal dari nama gunung (Gunung Muria), yang terletak di sebelah utara kota Kudus, Jawa Tengah, tempat Sunan Muria dimakamkan. Sunan Muria wafat pada tahun 1560 M.

Sunan Muria menikah dengan Dewi Sujinah putri Sunan Ngudung, adik dari Sunan Kudus dan Sunan Muria menikah dengan dewi Roroyono Putri Ki Ageng Ngerang dan Nyai Ageng Ngerang.[3] Sunan Muria menikah dengan dewi sujinah dikaruniai seorang anak bernama Raden Saridin,Syech Jangkung/Waliyullah Sunan Landoh.

Sedangkan, pernikahan Sunan Muria dengan dewi Roroyono Putri Ki Ageng Ngerang dan Nyai Ageng Ngerang dikaruniai tiga orang anak sunan nyamplungan, raden ayu nasiki,pangeran santri, Salah satu putra Sunan Muria yang terkenal ialah (Panembahan Pangulu) Pangeran Jogodipo , yang makamnya berada satu kompleks di Colo.

Sumber : Wikipedia
textTranslated:
The name Sunan Muria itself is thought to come from the name of the mountain (Mount Muria), which is located north of the city of Kudus, Central Java, where Sunan Muria was buried. Sunan Muria died in 1560 AD.

Sunan Muria married Dewi Sujinah daughter of Sunan Ngudung, sister of Sunan Kudus and Sunan Muria married the goddess Roroyono Putri Ki Ageng Ngerang and Nyai Ageng Ngerang.[3] Sunan Muria married the goddess Sujinah and was blessed with a child named Raden Saridin, Syech Jangkung/Waliyullah Sunan Landoh.

Meanwhile, the marriage of Sunan Muria with the goddess Roroyono Putri Ki Ageng Ngerang and Nyai Ageng Ngerang was blessed with three children sunan nyamapulung, raden ayu nasiki, prince santri, one of Sunan Muria's famous sons is (Panembahan Pangulu) Pangeran Jogodipo, whose tomb is in a complex in Colo.

Source: Wikipedia

text:
Jika ingin menelusuri jejak para penyebar agama Islam di tanah Jawa dan Indonesia, beliau ini adalah sosok yang tepat. Kanjeng Sunan Muria adalah satu dari 9 Sunan yg pernah dengan gigih menyebarkan Islam hingga bisa pesat seperti saat ini.
Semoga arwah para pendahulu tersebut kelak dikumpulkan bersama di surga bersama Rosululloh, kholifah, para sahabat dan orang-orang suci dan baik hingga akhir jaman nanti. Dan semoga kita semua diberikan hidayah dan kekuatan untuk menjalankan syariat Islam dengan baik dan benar tanpa terpengaruh dengan upaya menyudutkan dan mendiskreditkan Islam dg cara licik dan halus, agar kita bisa masuk menjadi bagian para orang sholeh dan bisa masuk surga yg abadi. Aamiin yra
textTranslated:
If you want to trace the footsteps of the spreaders of Islam in Java and Indonesia, he is the right figure. Kanjeng Sunan Muria is one of the 9 Sunans who have persistently spread Islam to the point where it is growing as fast as it is today.
Hopefully the spirits of these predecessors will be gathered together in heaven with Rosululloh, the caliph, friends and holy and good people until the end of time. And may we all be given guidance and strength to carry out Islamic law properly and correctly without being influenced by attempts to corner and discredit Islam in cunning and subtle ways, so that we can become part of the pious people and enter eternal heaven. Amen yra
title: Tomb of Sunan Muria

text: Sungguh Menakjubkan dan menegangkan  untuk bisa sampai ke tempat makam sunan Muria ini karena berada diatas gunung yang harus di tempuh dengan jalan kaki atau naik sepeda motor yang bikin bulu kuduk merinding dan ketar ketir serasa jantung mau copot saja dan serasa mau jatuh saja dari sepeda motor tapi syukur Alhamdulillah selamat sampai  keatas, dalam hati bicara kapok rasanya kesini kalau bigini, tapi setelah nyampai ke kampung, hati pengin kembali lagi... Luar biasa karomahnya waliullah...
textTranslated: It's really amazing and nerve-wracking to get to the place where Sunan Muria's grave is because it is on top of a mountain that has to be reached by walking or riding a motorbike which makes goosebumps and shivers feel like your heart is going to fall out and you feel like you're going to fall off the motorbike but Thank God, Alhamdulillah, we got safely up, in my heart I felt like I had given up coming here if it was big, but after arriving at the village, my heart wanted to go back again... Waliullah's character is extraordinary...

name: Mohammad Nur Alim
text:
Sunan Muria dilahirkan dengan nama Raden Umar Said. Menurut beberapa riwayat, dia adalah putra dari Sunan Kalijaga dari pernikahan dengan Dewi Saroh, putri Syekh Maulana Ishaq.

Meninggal: 1551

Kebangsaan: Indonesia

Lahir: Raden Umar Said

Tempat pemakaman: Makam Sunan Muria

Orang tua: Sunan Kalijaga, Dewi Saroh

Anak: Sunan Nyamplungan, Raden Ayu Nasiki, Pangeran Santri

Saudara kandung: Dewi Sofiah, Dewi Rakayuh
textTranslated:
Sunan Muria was born with the name Raden Umar Said. According to several traditions, he was the son of Sunan Kalijaga from his marriage to Dewi Saroh, the daughter of Sheikh Maulana Ishaq.

Died: 1551

Nationality: Indonesian

Born: Raden Umar Said

Burial place: Sunan Muria Tomb

Parents: Sunan Kalijaga, Dewi Saroh

Children: Sunan Nyamplungan, Raden Ayu Nasiki, Prince Santri

Siblings: Dewi Sofiah, Dewi Rakayuh
title: Tomb of Sunan Muria
